title: one pot spaghetti
directions: Put ground beef in a large frying pan.
Break it into small pieces.
Add onion.
Cook over low heat until all the red is gone from the meat.
Add salt, pepper and mustard.
Stir.
Add uncooked spaghetti.
Add water and tomato juice.
Cover and cook over medium heat.
Cook until mixture begins to boil.
Turn heat to low.
Cook fifteen minutes.
Stir some as it cooks.
Add cheese to spaghetti mixture.

title: caramel custard flan
directions: Caramelize sugar over medium heat.
Pour into Pyrex pie pan and tip quickly to coat bottom.
Blend rest of ingredients in blender for 7 minutes and pour over caramelized sugar.
Place pan in 1/2-inch water bath and bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Invert to serve.

title: double boiler frosting
directions: Place first 4 ingredients over boiling water and beat with rotary beater until mixture stands in stiff peaks.
Scrape bottom and sides of pan occasionally.
Fold in vanilla.
Frost as usually done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese; beat in peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Add milk slowly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Garnish and refrigerate.
This is soooo good.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Combine sugar and flour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Pour small amount of juice over mixture. Sprinkle crackers on top.
Pour butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook and stir hamburg and onion over medium heat.
Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper. Spread in a pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs and baking mix until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Top with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: potato soup with leeks
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook about 5 minutes (do not brown).
Add leeks; cook 5 minutes more.
Add potatoes; add flour.
Add seasoning and hot beef broth.
Bring to boil and simmer until done.
Add chopped chives and parsley when serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Crumble Italian sausage into 2 cup measure.
Cover loosely and microwave on High (100%), stirring every minute, until done, 3 to 4 minutes; break up and drain.
Spread 1 tablespoon pizza sauce over each English muffin half.
Sprinkle with cooked sausage.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Place on plate, microwave uncovered on High (100%) until cheese is melted and bubbly, 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: quick nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Mix at low speed until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 or 60 minutes until bread springs back when lightly touched.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: baked swiss chicken breasts
directions: Divide chicken breasts in half.
Place the 8 chicken breast halves in a 9 x 13-inch casserole, which has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with Swiss cheese slices.
Mix wine and soup (undiluted) and pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with dry dressing mix.
Drizzle margarine over dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Can be made a day in advance.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into 3 or 4 loaf pans. Bake at 325° for about 25 to 35 minutes or until bounces back or toothpick comes out clean.

title: sweet-sour spareribs
directions: Blend cornstarch, vinegar and water in saucepan.
Add pineapple, sugar, catsup and soy sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Baste spareribs with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting and turning several times.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix with hands.
If too sticky, add extra dry milk.
Can be eaten.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: rice and bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove from pan and drain all but 2 tablespoons of oil.
Mix the rest of ingredients in pan.
Cook, stirring until well coated.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crumble bacon over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake the brownies according to package instructions.
Make the chocolate mousse as directed.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt butter, water and caramels in double boiler.
Add nuts and mix well with fork.
Drop on wax paper.
Let cool completely. Dip in melted chocolate.

title: bailey's irish creme
directions: Combine all in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator up to 1 month.
Makes 5 cups.

title: canned peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon in saucepan.
Stir in sliced fruit.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour into crust. Dot with butter.
Put top crust on and bake about 40 minutes at 425° until nicely browned.

title: special cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain grease.
Melt together cheeses and Ro-Tel.
Add sausage after melted.
Serve with chips.

title: no bake orange balls
directions: Mix wafer crumbs, coconut and powdered sugar.
Add undiluted orange juice and mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in additional powdered sugar.
Store in covered container overnight. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: black cherry gelatin dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add orange and cherry juice. Add cherries; stir at intervals to keep them evenly distributed until mixture begins to gel.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: veggie pizza
directions: In an ungreased 17 x 11 x 1 inch pan, spread crescent roll dough (do not separate along perforations).
Press dough mixture to spread over bottom of the pan to form a seamless crust for the pizza.
Bake according to directions on dough can.
Let baked crust cool.

title: quick baked apple
directions: In a small bowl, combine nuts, raisins and coconut; set aside.
Core apple and peel the top third.
Place in a microwave safe dish.
Fill center with nut mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour apple juice into dish, pour syrup over apple. Cover and microwave on high for 2-3 minutes or until apple is tender, basting and rotating each minute.
Serve warm.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts, chill until firm, shape into balls and roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: tuna steaks with mustard butter
directions: In container (not aluminum), that is large enough to hold tuna in a single layer, arrange tuna.
In cup or small bowl, combine soy sauce, vinegar and ginger; pour over tuna.
Let stand for 5 minutes; turn tuna over and let stand 5 minutes longer.
In cup or small bowl, combine 2 teaspoons butter and the mustard; mix until combined.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: browned rice
directions: Wash rice.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Heat fat or salad oil in a deep heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Add rice; stir over low heat until each rice kernel is golden brown.
Add boiling water slowly. Add salt.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Do not stir.
The rice
should have absorbed all the water and be dry and flaky. Makes 6 servings.

title: supermoist chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix about half of the cake mix with margarine, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes (centers will be soft).
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: oven baked rice
directions: Saute rice, margarine and onions until brown, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.
Stir occasionally.

title: chops 'n rice(for 2)
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper and brown in skillet. Put raw rice in greased baking dish; add chops.
Rinse skillet with 1/2 cup water.
Pour over rice.
Add consomme, cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice and tomato soup
directions: Cook rice with beef broth until brown and then add together all the other ingredients.
Cook about 18 minutes.

title: beef a la easy
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 4 hours or you can make in a crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt, using a pastry blender or 2 knives.
Combine the beaten egg, vinegar and water.
Pour liquid mixture into flour mixture all at once.
Blend with fork.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put everything in a bowl and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion until clear.
Add seasonings.
Add chopped tomatoes, corn and beans.
Add chilies.

title: grandma sosolik's pickles
directions: To one quart of cucumbers (ends cut off) add 1 tablespoon Morton's salt, 2 cloves garlic and fresh dill.
Add one-third white vinegar and fill with water (well water preferred).
Seal jars.
Put on stove in pot of cold water.
Boil until cucumbers turn a light color.
Remove jars from hot water and let cool.

title: herbed cheese omelet
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add
next
5 ingredients, mixing well.
Combine eggs, water
and
teaspoon
ground white pepper; stir with a wire whisk
or	fork
until blended. Heat a 10-inch heavy skillet over medium heat until hot enough to	sizzle a	drop
of
water.
Add
olive oil and butter and rotate pan to coat bottom.
Pour egg mixture into skillet.
As mixture
starts to	cook,
gently lift edges of omelet with a spatula
and	tilt pan
so uncooked portion flows underneath. Spoon
cheese
mixture in center and fold sides over filling. Sprinkle with green onions and serve.	Yield:	4 servings.

title: cherry salad
directions: Blend cherry pie filling and condensed milk together.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip and pecans.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: yummy apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix gently, but well. Chill.
Looks nice in glass serving dish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fantail bread
directions: Mix sugar, Mazola oil and salt well.
Scald milk and water; cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle yeast in and stir to dissolve. Mix with sugar, oil and salt; stir well (it is easier to sift yeast in with the flour).
Add flour (pretty stiff).
Let rise until double in bulk, turn out on floured board and knead.
Have 3 pans greased.
Divide dough in 3 equal portions, then divide into 10 pieces and stack in pan.
Set in a warm place and let rise until double in bulk.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Mix dry ingredients and add to beaten egg yolks.
Gradually add the scalded milk, stirring constantly.
When cool, gradually add lemon juice and rind, mixing thoroughly.
Now fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a pan of hot water in a slow oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Chill before serving.
If pudding has not browned on top within 45 minutes, turn on broiler for a minute or two to have it a beautiful golden brown.
Serve with a lemon sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Beat the pudding, cream cheese, milk and sugar together for 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 of cookie crumbs into bottom of dish.
Pour mixture on top.
Add remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Put into freezer until ready to serve.
This can also be kept in refrigerator and not frozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute butter, onions, celery and broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: rice and oyster dressing
directions: Melt butter and add onions, celery and green peppers.
Cook until soft or turned color.
Add drained oysters and cooked chopped giblets.
Pour over cooked rice and add fresh parsley. Mix very well with salt and pepper to taste and a little cayenne pepper.
If dressing is too dry, add some of liquid from oysters or liquid from cooked giblets.
Stuff turkey or chicken or serve as a side dish with any fowl or meat.
Makes 7 to 10 servings.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into balls.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni noodles as directed on package.
In a deep casserole, layer macaroni noodles and cheese (3 layers of each), ending with cheese.
In another bowl, mix together milk and egg. Pour this over macaroni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Place chicken in pot and cover well with water.
Add salt and boil chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Dip tortillas in hot broth (do not allow tortillas to remain in broth or they will tear apart) and line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with totrillas.
Combine soups and garlic juice and spread over chicken.
Combine onion and bell pepper.
Place evenly over top of soup layer.
Add cheese in even layer.
Mash tomatoes. Combine with chicken broth.
Pour over top of mixture.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for about 30 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apple crumble
directions: Butter 2-quart baking dish and spread apples.
Mix salt, cinnamon, spice and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over apples.
Add water.
Mix flour, sugar and egg until crumbly and spread over apples.
Pour melted margarine over crumbly topping.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold with whipped topping or ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry-rice cream
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in double boiler. Cover and cook over simmering water for 40 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir occasionally.
Mix gelatin and sugar; stir into rice until gelatin dissolves.
Pour into a large bowl; cool.
Add vanilla. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into 8-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.

title: grandma's bar-b-q sauce for pork
directions: Mix together, and pour over pork before baking.
Good for roasts, spareribs, shoulder, etc.

title: coconut fruit salad surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add whipped cream topping.

title: cottage cheese lunch loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form loaf on flat serving dish.
Chill 3 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: steak diane
directions: Melt butter in large, nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and garlic; cook 2 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms.
Cook and stir 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove and set aside.

title: cucumber lime pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamelware overnight.
(Do not use aluminum ware.)
Wash 3 times in clean water and soak in fresh ice water for 3 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a low boil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add cucumbers and soak overnight.
Boil pickles in liquid for 35 minutes.
Fill sterilized jars and seal.

title: gold nugget meat pie
directions: Soften bread crumbs in milk; add meat, egg, 2 tablespoons grated onion, 1 teaspoon salt, Worcestershire sauce and catsup and mix well. Line the bottom and sides of 10-inch pie plate with mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: parmesan baked chicken breasts
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix cheese, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in margarine.
Roll in cheese mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: stove top green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except onions in large saucepan.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Just before serving, add and stir in onions.

title: clayton knight's peoples choice chili
directions: Brown blade
steak.
Trim off fat and skin.
Unseasoned tenderizer may
be	added
before
preparation.
Blend or chop bell pepper, onion and garlic; set mixture aside.
Pour tomato juice in Dutch oven
and
chopped
tomatoes.
Now
add browned meat and at this
point
put Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add chili powder and
ground
cumin.
Now
add	the mixture of bell pepper, onion
and	garlic	cloves.
Add red kidney beans and Tabasco sauce.
As	chili
cooks, add more tomato juice or crushed tomatoes to make consistency of chili just the way you like it.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain beans, corn and water chestnuts and mix together.
Mix sour cream and soup together and pour on top of vegetables and mix together.
Put mixture in baking dish.
Crush up one package of Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Brown steak, onion and celery in oil.
Add sugar, water, pepper and bouillon cube.	Simmer for 45 minutes.	Add green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.	Blend together 1/2 cup water, cornstarch and soy sauce. Add to steak.
Stir until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: spinach balls
directions: In large frypan, melt margarine; saute onion and remove from heat.
Cook and drain spinach and set aside.
Mix all ingredients (you may use the frypan) by hand.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Roll mixture into small walnut sized balls (the smaller the better).
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Freeze leftovers.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.

title: french parmesan bread
directions: Mix butter, cheese and garlic salt.
Cut French bread in slices, making sure that you don't cut through the bottom.
Spread the cheese mixture between the slices.
Bake in a 325° oven until the butter is melted.
Serve hot.

title: skillet fish dinner
directions: Heat oil in a
large
skillet
over
medium
heat.
Add onion and garlic;
saute
until
onion
is
crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes, cover; reduce
heat.
Simmer
about
3 minutes.
Cut fish into 4 equal portions; place on vegetables.
Cut each ear of corn into 4 pieces;
add
to vegetables.
Add olives, dill weed and pepper. Cover and
simmer
10 to 15 minutes or until fish turns opaque. Fish
is
done
when it flakes easily when tested with a fork. Yields 4 servings, 237 calories.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cut together 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and butter (as for pie crust).
Press with heel of hand in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix together eggs, 2 cups sugar, 1/4 cup flour, and baking powder, then stir in ReaLemon. Pour over hot crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate!

title: raisin ruff cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and soda; blend in. Add milk and vanilla.
Stir in oatmeal and raisins.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Also good if chocolate or butterscotch chips are added.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Shake remaining ingredients in a jar.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill. Makes 12 servings and will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: creole sauce for meats
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in salad oil until tender, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 20 minutes or until thick.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar and coloring, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Lastly, add mint chips.
Mini chips also work well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Put cookie mixture on greased cookie sheets.
Set in oven and turn off heat.
Do not open oven door for at least 5 hours or overnight.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions and strain. Meanwhile, melt butter and saute onion and bell pepper.
Heat soup and add 1/2 of the cheese to the heated soup.
Add sauteed vegetables.
Add spaghetti, chicken and pimiento.
Pour into a pan sprayed with Pam.
Top with the remaining cheese and add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 25 minutes and uncovered for 10 minutes or until cheese browns slightly.

title: sugar cookies(cut outs)
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Take small amount of dough out at a time.
Roll and cut out.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° to 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in hot water until soft, a few minutes. Drain on paper towels until dry.
Combine meats, salt, pepper, rice and eggs and mix well. Place 2 tablespoons of mixture in each cabbage leaf.
Roll leaf around meat and tuck in the ends.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and salt.
Beat in egg and vanilla; blend well.
Stir in flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add in drained pineapple and nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until very lightly browned.
Frost with powdered sugar and pineapple juice while cookies are still warm.

title: hot melt sandwiches
directions: Spread buns with butter.
In bowl, mix sauce, butter and poppy seed.
Set aside.
Place meat and cheese on buns.
Place in pan. Pour sauce over them.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken divan casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender in water seasoned with parsley, onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain and break chicken into strips or pieces.
Boil broccoli until fork-tender; drain. Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs; set aside.
Mix soup, shredded cheese, sour cream and lemon juice and heat.
Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole with Pam.
Put a layer of broccoli, one layer of chicken and pour soup mixture over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and finely sprinkle Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place cut up chicken in baking dish.
Mix together the cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and put on top of chicken mixture.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cucumber sweet relish
directions: Coarse grind cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Add canning salt. Mix and let set 30 minutes.

title: harvest cookies
directions: Cream
together
the shortening and sugar.
Beat in the eggs and pumpkin.
Add the vanilla.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, baking
powder,
baking
soda
and salt; add to the mixture. Stir in the raisins, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a	350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until they test done.

title: jean's marinated vegetables
directions: Clean vegetables and mix all ingredients well.
Marinate in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: broiled striped bass
directions: Spray broiling pan with Pam. Place fish skin side down. Drizzle each fillet with lemon juice. Drizzle each fillet with butter. Sprinkle with Parmesan and paprika. Salt and pepper to taste. Broil fillets on top rack for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin eggnog pie with ginger cream
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into pie shell.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, butter and eggs.
Add to milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until done.
Add vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: Freeze cookies and grind in a food processor or blender until it looks like "dirt."
In a separate bowl, mix softened cream cheese; add pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Beat until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Put a layer of cookie mixture in bottom of pan (or flower pot), then add a layer of pudding mixture.
Continue to layer, ending with a cookie mixture layer on top.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted butter to make crust.
Layer with sliced bananas.
Beat confectioners sugar, 2 sticks butter and eggs at high speed for 15 minutes.
Hand stir pineapple (drained) into mixture.
Spread over bananas.
Layer with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped cherries and nuts. Chill.

title: mushroom bread wedges
directions: Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles & place on a greased 12-inch round pizza pan, with points toward the center. Seal perforations. In a bowl, combine the mushroom & butter; toss to coat. Spoon mushroom mixture over dough. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese & Italian seasoning. Bake at 375 degrees for 15-20 minutes or until crust is golden brown & mushrooms are tender. Yield: 8 servings.

title: marshmallow cake
directions: Beat sugar with eggs.
Add melted margarine.
Add flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Beat with blender until well mixed.
Add batter to 12 x 8-inch greased pan.
Top with marshmallows cut in half.
Mix brown sugar and nuts and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for
40 to 50 minutes.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Melt cheese in microwave oven or on top of stove.
Pour remaining ingredients in melted cheese; mix well.

title: braggin' beans
directions: Combine kidney beans with onions and chopped bell pepper.
Add bacon, chili sauce, garlic, dark brown sugar and flavoring.
Place in heavy skillet and bring to a boil.
Turn down heat.
Cover and cook gently, stirring, about 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: black-eyed peas with ground meat
directions: Lightly brown meat.
Add onions, bell pepper and tomatoes. Cook 20 minutes.
Add steak sauce, peas and celery.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: baked chicken(excellent for heart patient)
directions: Remove	skin.
Salt very lightly.
Sprinkle
with
your favorite
poultry seasoning.
Roll with
a	rolling
pin
Rice Krispies.
Coat chicken with the Rice Krispies.
Place chicken in a pan lined with foil and bake at 375° for an hour.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Boil water, sugar and salt until it forms a hard ball in water (250°).
Place marshmallow cream in bowl and stir in hot syrup. Continue stirring until slightly stiff (holds a peak).
Fold in nuts, food coloring and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper on buttered pan.
After it is cooled and set, store and place in refrigerator.

title: mushroom rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until water is absorbed.
Stir occasionally while baking.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in Dutch oven (frying pan). Add chicken and cook until brown, remove chicken.
Add onion and garlic and cook until onion is soft.
Add green pepper and tomato, cook, stirring, until liquid evaporates.
Add rice and coat with vegetables.
Add broth, bay leaf and salt; bring to a boil.
Pour in shallow baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top with pimento for garnish and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine in a heavy skillet, the sugar, cocoa, milk, syrup and margarine.
Mix and let come to a boil.
Let mix boil for 5 minutes or until soft ball stage (238°).
Stir only until sugar dissolves. After mix has reached soft ball stage, set off burner to cool until you can place hand on bottom of skillet.
Beat until mixture loses its shine.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered dish and cut into squares when hard.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Add soda to buttermilk and set aside.
Cream sugar and Crisco. Add eggs one at a time.
Add other ingredients.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Makes 4 layers.
Bake at 350° about 15 or 20 minutes.
Top with Fudge Frosting.

title: curried potatoes and peas
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water to cover over medium heat until tender (about 15 minutes).
Heat margarine in skillet; add onion and cook until softened (about 5 minutes).
Stir in curry powder and honey; cook about 1 minute.
Drain potatoes; toss with peas to coat with onion mixture.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Cream Crisco and brown sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour, baking soda and oatmeal.
Set aside and make filling.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Mix cake according
to	package,
using pineapple juice for liquid and water to
make
up
liquid
amount.
Grease and flour 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool in pan. Blend cream cheese,
pudding mix and cold milk together. Fold in drained pineapple;	spread	over
top
of cooled cake. Cover
with Cool
Whip.
Sprinkle
with
nuts
and
coconut. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Place oil in a deep skillet and add water, green pepper, tomatoes, eggplant, onion, garlic and spices.
Cook at medium heat until most of water is absorbed.
Lower heat and simmer, stirring often.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil
garden
spirals
for
minutes; drain but don't cool. Mix salad dressing with milk, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper. Pour
over
pasta
and
mix
well.
Fold in all other ingredients, Parmesan cheese last.
Cover and cool for several hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken cordon blue(in microwave)
directions: Pound each chicken breast until flattened and place 1/2 cheese slice and slice of ham on chicken, then fold each breast in half and roll together.
Put butter in micro-proof baking dish and melt. Place each chicken breast in pan and cook on High, covered, for 10 minutes.
Blend soup and mushrooms with juice of chicken together and pour over chicken and cook 4 minutes on High.
Stir chicken juice with soup and mushrooms to be used as gravy.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent roll on a cookie sheet.
Press together. Bake and let cool.

title: percy's country fried potatoes
directions: Mix onion with potatoes.
Heat large black iron skillet. Grease skillet with lard.
Add potatoes and onions.
Put lard on top of potatoes and onions.
Add salt and pepper.
Put lid on and cook slowly until well done, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pavlova
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar together in bowl until the whites hold a stiff peak.
Add the sugar gradually, beating until mixture becomes stiff and glossy.
Beat in cornstarch, then vinegar and vanilla.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
This is good with vegetables.

title: mushroom goulash with eggplant
directions: Combine mushrooms, eggplant, tomatoes, green peppers and garlic.
Simmer in fat; season with salt, pepper and marjoram. Cook for 20 minutes.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add pineapple juice then chill.
Pour over ice in a punch bowl adding chilled ginger ale. For an extra special punch, pour over 2 to 3 pints of sherbet.

title: decorator's buttercream icing
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then add liquid plus shortening and beat.
Don't overbeat or you may have air bubbles in your icing. Can add icing food coloring found in cake decorator's section of your store to decorate your cake with any color(s) you like.

title: no peek beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine all ingredients, except sour cream and noodles or rice.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Cover. Bake for 3 hours.
Do not peek! Remove from oven.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and cooking oil; add eggs, beating well after each.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Add lemon or vanilla extract to taste.
Pour into large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand in pan for 20 minutes before removing.

title: energy trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 3/4 quarts.

title: chow mein noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef in large skillet and drain.
Add all other ingredients to beef.
Stir and pour in 2-quart dish to bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 325° for about 30 minutes.
(Don't overcook, it will become dry.)

title: cheese bread cubes
directions: Cut crusts off French bread.
Cut bread in 2-inch squares and freeze.
Add cheese to butter and mix well.
When bread is frozen, spread cheese mixture on all sides but the bottom of the cube. Return to freezer.
Just before serving, bake at 400° for 15 minutes, watching carefully.
Serve with salsa or soup or as a snack.

title: cider punch
directions: Mix together in a large crock-pot.
Cook on low.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir in yeast.
Knead 5 minutes, until smooth.
Let rise until double.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thick. Cut doughnuts with cutter.
Let rise 30 to 35 minutes.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Dust with sugar and cinnamon.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs and beat well. Sift flour, salt and cocoa together.

Add to sugar mixture, mixing well. Fold in vanilla and nuts. Pour batter into a greased 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch greased pan. Bake in 300° to 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done. Remove from oven. Place marshmallows evenly over the top of cake and return to the oven for 5 to 10
minutes, just until marshmallows melt. Remove from the oven; cool and frost.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Add butter flavoring to soda and buttermilk.
Cream shortening, butter and eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk mixture alternately.
Add flavorings and sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (test for doneness).

title: crispy chicken
directions: Put stuffing in blender or food processor to make fine crumbs. Dip chicken, piece by piece, in butter and roll it in crumbs until covered.
Place in shallow baking pan or cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 4.

title: hawaiian hash
directions: Drain fruits.
Mix fruits with rest of ingredients. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain well.
Combine beef mixture and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon bean mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield 4 to 6 servings.

title: my moma's pickled green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes thin. Soak in water and lime for 24 hours. Drain and soak in fresh water for 4 hours, changing water every hour. Make syrup of sugar, vinegar and pickling spice. Bring to boil and pour over tomatoes. Let stand overnight in syrup. Next morning, boil gently for 1 hour. Put in sterilized jars; cover with syrup and seal.

title: loaded potato soup
directions: Combine ingredients (except bacon) in large pan and cook until potatoes are tender.
In the meantime, cook bacon.
When done, crumble bacon and cheese to taste (about one cup of cheese).
Very good served with corn bread.

title: susan's refrigerator rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, Susan combines the hot potato water (drained from boiled potatoes), sugar and salt, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
When it has cooled to lukewarm, she crumbles the fresh yeast cakes into it, lets them soften (about 5 minutes), then stirs in the beaten egg.

title: sauteed zucchini strips(low calorie, low sodium)
directions: Wash the zucchini, but do not peel.
Cut into strips 1/3 inch wide by 2 1/2 inches long.
Heat vegetable oil in skillet; saute zucchini strips on low heat until browned on all sides.
Add pepper, oregano and garlic.
Cook an additional 5 minutes on low heat.
Serves 4.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Serve with bagels or crackers.
This can be easily doubled.

title: korozotes
directions: Blend all ingredients together for a creamy spread on crackers or bread.
Can also be used as a dip by adding a tablespoon more of margarine.

title: bunker hill lemon chill
directions: To make crust, press 1 stick of margarine, flour and 3/4 cup pecans into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread cream cheese mixture on crust while crust is still warm.
Mix Jell-O instant pudding and milk (do not follow instructions on box).
Let stand 5 minutes; then spread over cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip and chopped pecans.

title: brother stan's crawfish gumbo
directions: Fry okra 15 minutes in cooking oil.
Use large aluminum pot. Dump into bowl and use pot for next step.
Melt margarine; add flour to make light brown roux.
Add bell pepper and white and green onions; stir together.
Combine cooked okra; cook for 5 minutes.
Add 2 quarts water and bring to a boil.
Add crab boil, garlic, salt and chicken.
Cook one hour.
Put in crawfish tails and oysters.
Let simmer 15 minutes.
Add gumbo file; stir and serve over rice in a large bowl.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour into 10-inch iron skillet or pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: choucroute garni
directions: Soak sauerkraut for 5 minutes in cold water.
Drain well. Place ham hocks in a Dutch oven or large casserole.
Add drained sauerkraut, wine and bay leaf.
Press cloves into onion; press onion down into sauerkraut.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer very slowly 1 1/2 hours, tossing with fork once or twice.
Cut knockwurst and place on sauerkraut.
Simmer 20 minutes longer.
Add apples, pushing them down into sauerkraut.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Scrub potatoes well.
Cook in boiling, salted water for 20 minutes.
Arrange Choucroute with potatoes on a large deep platter.
Serve with wheat bread and mustard.

title: lime sauce
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Delicious with artichokes and raw vegetables.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender; drain.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in the flour, salt and pepper.
Add 2 cups milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Mix cheese sauce with macaroni.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
(At this point can be topped with sliced tomato and sprinkled with salt.)
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: fudgy pecan cake
directions: Line bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan with tinfoil.
Butter foil and sides of pan.
Set aside.
Combine 3/4 cup of butter, sugar and vanilla in a large mixer bowl; beat well.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in 1/2 cup cocoa, flour, oil and water; beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt in small mixer bowl until stiff peaks form.
Carefully fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.
Cover; chill until firm.
Remove side of pan.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening; add sugar and blend.
Add eggs one at a time, beat after each egg.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together three times.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour into greased, lightly floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy, but not stiff.
Add water and beat a little longer.
Fold in pecans.
Mix until well coated. Mix
in remaining ingredients.
Place on buttered cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 225°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour. Mix well. Stir in eggs and butter. Add chocolate chips, pecans and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into the 2 pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Stir in cornstarch and cook until bubbly.
Stir in undiluted apple juice concentrate and raisins.
Heat to a boil and cook until thickened. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Peel apples, cut in half and remove cores.
Cut apples into thin wedges.
In a cup, mix flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a large bowl, toss apples with thickened cornstarch mixture, stir apples into raisin mixture until coated with sauce.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Fill crust with apple slices, spreading evenly.
Put on top crust.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cover pie loosely with foil and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until filling is bubbly and crust is golden.
Cool pie on rack.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast. Mix flour, sugar, butter and egg. Combine all ingredients. Put in airtight bowl; place in refrigerator. Dough is best if mixed at night and allowed to stand in refrigerator. Grease muffin tins and spoon out as many as needed. Bake at 350° until brown. Return remaining dough to refrigerator and use as needed. Will keep up to 6 days.

title: kringla
directions: Mix sour cream, buttermilk and sugar together.
Add sifted dry ingredients and stir well.
Take one heaping tablespoons of dough and roll out in a little flour.
Shape in figure 8.
Bake about 8 minutes at 475° on top shelf.

title: cooked frosting
directions: Blend milk and flour and cook over low heat until fairly thick white sauce forms.
While cooling, blend in separate bowls the Crisco and oleo, then in next bowl sugar and vanilla.
Add white sauce to all these ingredients and beat with electric beater.

title: turkey-broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook broccoli according to package. Layer in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Spread turkey evenly on top. Combine soup with milk until smooth and pour over turkey. Sprinkle with grated cheese atop.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, margarine, syrup,
salt and cream of tartar until a hard ball forms in cold water.
Remove from burner and stir
1 teaspoon soda (will foam).
Pour over popped popcorn. Place in
a large pan and bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat; drain, then cool.
Combine all ingredients except meat and mix well.
Have a large (10 to 12-inch) cast-iron skillet hot in a 350° oven with a small amount of grease in bottom of skillet so the cornbread won't stick.
Pour 1/4 batter mixture into skillet, then add 1/2 meat.
Repeat so batter mix is on top. Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: never fail hot rolls
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and salt.
Add boiling water; stir until creamy.
Add eggs; crumble yeast in warm water and dissolve.
Pour into mixture.
Alternate 1 cup cold water with flour.
Grease top and seal tightly.
Put in refrigerator; will keep a week.
Knead and make into rolls.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix apples, apple juice, thickener and spice; stir until apples are well coated. Add lemon juice to keep apples light colored.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Top with second crust.
Seal the edges and cut slits on top for steam.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes until golden brown.
One serving contains 220 calories, 1 1/2 fruit exchange, 1 bread exchange and 2 fat exchanges.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll
small
balls
of	dough
in
hands and flatten on cookie sheet with fork.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) until light brown, about 8 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together, then add in the rest of the ingredients and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat and drain, stir in seasonings, tomato sauce, and kidney beans.
Pour into 2 quart casserole.
Prepare muffin mix according to package.
Spread over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 5 minutes and serve topped with sour cream if desired.

title: angel food delight
directions: Just before serving, crush the Butterfinger candy bars into tiny pieces (leave in wrapper and hit with something heavy).
Add to Cool Whip and frost the angel food cake.
If you only want a piece at a time, leave Cool Whip mixture in bowl and refrigerate.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Cut wings at joints. Discard tips. Wash and pat dry wings. Arrange wings in a foil-lined pan in a single layer. Bake in oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: tiger butter candy
directions: Melt milk chocolate and white chocolate in two separate bowls in a 250° oven.
When completely melted, spread milk chocolate into a 12 x 12-inch pan.
Combine peanut butter with the white chocolate and pour mixture over milk chocolate layer.
With a knife, swirl until surface is white and dark chocolate swirls. Cool at room temperature and cut into 1-inch squares.
Keeps nicely in a tin in a cool, dry place.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 300° and uncovered for 1/2 hour.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Drain and chop maraschino cherries.
Combine cake mix, mincemeat, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in cherries, raisins and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on wire racks.

title: london fog
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Serve in tall glasses.
Delicious and refreshing.
May halve recipe.
Makes 12 or more servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with cut up vegetables or cup up Italian bread or pumpernickel bread.
May be served in a hollowed out round pumpernickel bread with the bread on the side.
Also good on baked potatoes; also on fish.

title: cream of crab-broccoli soup
directions: Cook frozen broccoli; drain and set aside. Saute onion in butter until transparent; blend in flour. Add milk gradually; stir and cook until thickened and smooth. (Use wire whisk.) Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot soup. Add seasonings, crab and broccoli; heat through but do not boil.

title: hermits(preparation time: 20 minutes. bake time: 7 to 8 minutes.)
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Cream butter flavor Crisco, sugar and milk in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended. Add eggs 1 at a time. Beat well after each addition. Combine flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Mix into creamed mixture. Stir in raisins and nuts. Drop level measuring tablespoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart onto ungreased sheet. Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes. Remove to cooling rack. Sift confectioners sugar over cooled cookies. Makes 4 1/2 to 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, salt and margarine real well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Add flour alternately with milk, adding flour first and last.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients. Cook for 2 minutes. Remove pan from fire; add the remaining ingredients. Stir well, then drop mixture from a spoon onto waxed paper, allowing cookies to cool. Makes 30 to 40 cookies. Try adding peanut butter; try 1/4 cup at the end of the cooking time.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles according to package and drain.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Then add noodles and mix all together.

title: mars coconut bars
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and coconut and refrigerate.
Melt chocolate bar with paraffin over hot water.
Make balls of first mixture and coat with chocolate mixture.

title: frozen pizza dough(fast, cheap, easy)
directions: Thaw bread in a plastic bag.
Do not close up the bag.
Leave it open so the dough can expand.
Thaw at either room temperature or in the refrigerator.

title: fruit curry
directions: Alternate fruits in a 3-quart casserole.
Arrange pineapple slices on top with a cherry in center of each slice. Combine sugar, curry powder and butter.
Sprinkle over the fruit.
Yields 16 servings.

title: drop donuts
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients in a large bowl, then add 8 cups flour, half at a time.
Let dough stand for a few minutes to take up moisture.
If it is thick enough to spoon up and drop in grease you won't need extra flour.
If not, add flour (a little at a time) until it becomes thick.
Then drop by teaspoons into hot grease. Turn and cook as needed.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together apples, 1/3 cup sugar, cinnamon, salt and melted butter.
Place in greased 8-inch square baking dish; set aside. Combine 3/4 cup sugar and flour; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and green peppers (drain fat).
In large bowl, mix together all soups well.
Pour into skillet.
Let simmer until hot.
Cook noodles by directions on package.
Drain noodles.
Serve hamburger mixture over noodles.

title: diabetic carrot pennies
directions: Place carrots in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with basil, salt and pepper.
Toss together.
Add water and dot with margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes, until fork-tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Sift together and add to egg mixture the flour, baking powder and salt. Heat milk and Crisco or butter to boiling point.
Add at once to egg mixture and blend thoroughly.
(Do not add more flour.)
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
While cake is hot, add syrup of brown sugar, cream and butter to top of cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top of syrup.
Place cake under broiler until coconut is golden (only takes a few seconds).

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water; drain.
Coat with butter. Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, mix soup, milk, onion, pepper and salt.
Cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tuna; combine with noodles and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top may be sprinkled with bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Cream together peanut butter and butter.
Add cracker crumbs and sugar.
Work mixture with hands and spread in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream wet ingredients together.
Mix dry ingredients together. Mix everything together.
Grease pans, 3 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch). Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Yum, yum, yum.

title: rancho roquefort dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Let ripen several hours before serving.

title: apple or pear butter
directions: Put fruit into a large pan.
Add apple juice; simmer until soft.
Mash with potato masher or with electric mixer.
Add the spices.
Serve over pancakes or on whole wheat toast.
Yields 16 cups.
Refrigerate.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients (1/2 of the Cool Whip) together and put in baked pie shell.
Let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, frost with rest of Cool Whip and decorate with lemon rind, shredded.

title: applesauce oatmeal bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In large bowl mix all ingredients together until well combined.
Pour into well greased 8-1/2x4-1/2x2-5/8-inch loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Serve with butter or cream cheese. Makes 1 loaf.

title: quick granola
directions: In large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients.
Add oil and honey and blend until moistened.
Spread on 2 ungreased 15 x 10-inch pans. Bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes, stirring once.
Cool.
Put in airtight container or freeze.
To make Granola Squares, beat 1/2 c. oleo, 1/2 c. brown sugar and 1/2 c. honey.
Add to above granola mix.
Spread in a greased 13x9x2 pan, press down firmly.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.
Mixture will be soft in center, but will firm when cooled.
Cut into squares.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk; beat at moderate speed for 2 minutes. Blend in Cool Whip.
Butter the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan; line with graham crackers.
Pour in 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Place another layer of crackers on top and add the rest of the pudding mixture.
Cover with another layer of graham crackers. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cover with ready made milk chocolate icing.

title: creamy chicken and biscuits
directions: Heat soups, chicken, peas, sour cream, 1 cup milk, salt and pepper to boiling in a saucepan.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boil, add jello and cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour in 2 qt. dish and refrigerate.

title: venison in red wine
directions: Toss meat cubes in flour.
Brown lightly in butter.
Add onion, parsley, garlic, bay leaf, salt and mushrooms.
Cook until onion is just tender.
Slowly add wine and water, stirring constantly.
Bring just to boiling; reduce heat and simmer until meat is tender.
Add more wine if necessary.
Remove bay leaf. Serve over hot cooked rice or hot buttered noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zeppole
directions: Night Before:
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Add flour to remaining water all at once.
Add Anisette and water with the yeast; beat vigorously until smooth.
Cover with cloth; place in warm area overnight.
dough should rise to about 2 times original size.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix well in blender.

title: barbecue leftovers
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons butter or margarine in a large skillet. Add chopped vegetables and cook.
Stir 5 minutes.
Stir in the catsup, water, brown sugar and vinegar; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer about 30 minutes longer, covered.
Stir once or twice.
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes or toast. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on the box and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Before cake is done, bring pineapple and sugar to boil for 5 minutes.

title: heavenly hash browned potatoes in the oven
directions: Place hash browns, 1/4 cup margarine, onion, pepper, cheese, sour cream and soup in large greased baking dish.
Mix until well blended.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons margarine with cereal or cracker crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until bubbly.

title: salad pizza
directions: Press dough on cookie sheet to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Gradually add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Blend in water and vanilla.
Combine flour and chopped nuts.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly until with lightly floured hands.
Break off small pieces of dough and shape them like dates.
Place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet; bake them 10 to 15 minutes (or until very light brown) in a 325° oven.
While still warm, roll the cookies in granulated sugar.

title: maureen's pork chops 'n stuffing
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Place into shallow baking dish. (Sometimes I do mine in electric skillet.)
Lightly mix together bread cubes, onion, butter, 1/4 cup water and poultry seasoning. Place a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over chops.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy ice cream
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add mashed bananas and strawberries; finish filling freezer with milk.
Freeze.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar and salt, making sure there are no lumps.
Slightly beat egg yolks and add to milk.
Slowly add milk mixture to dry ingredients; beat well.
Cook in heavy saucepan over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar and vanilla, again beating until stiff.
Spread over pie and bake at 350° until meringue is brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix oil and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs separately.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Then blend mixtures and beat thoroughly.
Stir in carrots.
Pour into three 8-inch or two 9-inch greased, floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg yolks and blend thoroughly.
Cream.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat egg whites in separate bowl.
Whip cream in another bowl.
Fold whipped cream and egg whites into first bowl, one at a time.
Crush 20 graham crackers.
Put half to 3/4 of them on the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put remainder on top.
Freeze.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix undrained pineapple, sugar and jello.
Cool but do not let jell.
Add buttermilk and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill.

title: strawberries and cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
(Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.)
Do not remove cake from pan.
When cake has cooled completely, poke holes in top of cake using handle of wooden spoon.
Pour berries and juice over top of cake.
Sift powdered sugar into Cool Whip and fold together.
Spread over top of cake.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: ham broccoli luncheon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam broccoli until tender; do not allow to change color.
In shallow pan, lay 2 pieces of ham per person, then 1 slice of Swiss on top.
Place 2 broccoli spears (flowerets on outside) in the middle; set aside.
In pan, melt the butter.
Blend in the flour, salt, horseradish, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and grated onion.
In a bowl, whip up the egg yolk and pineapple juice.
On very low flame, slowly blend bowl mixture into pan mixture.
Add the milk; cook on low heat.
Pour a little sauce over the broccoli, then roll up and hold with toothpicks.
Cook for 25 minutes.
Reheat remaining sauce and serve over rolls.
Serves 2 people.

title: emily's "spicy chicken spaghetti"
directions: Boil chicken for approximately 45 minutes.
Cool and tear apart.
Boil spaghetti as directed.
Saute onion in butter. Combine all ingredients in a large ovenproof dish and bake until cheese bubbles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix together hot water, sugar, salt and shortening. Cool until lukewarm. Sprinkle or crumble yeast into the warm water and stir until dissolved and then add to the first mixture. Add the egg and 1/2 the flour. Beat until smooth. Stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough. Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes. Place dough in a greased bowl and turn to grease the top of the dough. Cover tight with foil or waxed paper. Store in the fridge until needed or until it has doubled in bulk. Punch down dough and cut off what is needed and shape into rolls. Let rise in a cool place 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown. Keep in the fridge. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: maggie's special salad
directions: In a small saucepan mix sugar and cornstarch.
Then blend in 1 cup water and the vinegar.
Cook, stirring, until boiling and thickened.
Transfer to a small bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim all fat from steak; cut across grain in slices about 1 x 1/4-inch.
Add soy sauce and garlic and set aside.
Prepare vegetables.
Heat half the oil until very hot in large skillet. Add vegetables and stir-fry 2 minutes; remove from skillet to warm pan.
Add remaining oil to skillet; heat.
Add steak and stir-fry 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; add to steak.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add vegetables; mix thoroughly; serve over rice.
Calorie count does not include rice. Makes 4 servings (1 cup each); 281 calories and 17.8 grams fat.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Mix dressing.
Chop vegetables.
Cool pasta and mix all ingredients, except tomatoes.
Let mixture marinate 8 hours or overnight.
Add tomatoes 1 hour before serving.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Beat according to cake mix directions.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until test pick comes out clean.
This cake may be frosted with a glaze, cream cheese frosting or dust with powdered sugar.

title: cherry christmas cookies
directions: Melt cheese and butter.
Mix together and add flour; knead with hands like bread dough.
Refrigerate 1 to 3 hours.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; press with thumb.
Add cherry.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Make white frosting with milk, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Drizzle over cookies when cool.

title: ginger cutouts
directions: Melt shortening and mix with molasses and brown sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add soda to boiling water and add to first mixture.
Sift dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover and refrigerate.
Let age several days. Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out and decorate as desired.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Watch carefully.

title: chocolate crazy cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost with favorite icing recipe.

title: pate beau monde
directions: Blend cheese, water and Beau Monde together.
Add seasonings and parsley; mix well.
Chill.
Serve on crackers, bread or celery.

title: punch
directions: Mix well; serve with lime or pineapple sherbet.

title: piccalilli
directions: You will need sterile 12 pint jars.
Keep in boiling water until filled.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in a large heavy skillet.
Cook slowly over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking until mixture reaches soft ball stage (240°) or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball.
Add peanuts and salt.
Cook to the crack stage (290° to 300°) or until small amount dropped in very cold water separates and threads which are hard and brittle.
Watch mixture to keep from burning.
Add butter and soda, stirring to blend.
While still warm, pour into 2 large pans.
Pull to desired thickness.
When cold, crack into pieces.

title: layered cherry dessert
directions: Mix flour and margarine until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; let cool.
Mix 10x sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese with mixer.
Pour over crust.
Mix vanilla pudding with milk; pour over first layer.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Dice 1/2 cake in small cubes.
Place at the bottom of a large punch bowl.
Drain canned fruit and layer.
Rinse and cut strawberries; layer 1 pint strawberries.
Cover the first layer with a tub Cool Whip; repeat these steps again.

title: spiced grape jelly
directions: Remove stems and wash grapes.
Put grapes in preserving kettle with vinegar and spices.
Cook until soft.
Press through jelly bag and strain.
Boil liquid 20 minutes.
Measure and add one cup sugar for each cup of juice.
Boil rapidly to jelly stage.
Pour into jelly glasses.

title: bouillon sauce
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water; pour 3/4 cup in small saucepan.
Stir cornstarch in remaining broth.
Add to remaining broth; add sugar and oyster sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until thickened and bubbly.

title: volcano punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice and limeade.
Stir in ginger ale.
Add scoops of sherbet.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: momo kirkley's chocolate syrup(club member: laine)
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly, then add water. Cook on medium heat until thick. Add vanilla. When syrup is thick "eat with homemade biscuits".

title: black olive dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill 2 hours. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolatey velvet ice cream
directions: Combine whipping cream, sweetened condensed milk and chocolate syrup.
Beat with an electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Transfer to an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan; freeze until firm.
Makes 1 quart (8 servings).

title: carrot and sunflower seed salad
directions: Combine garlic, pepper, salt, vinegar and oil in bowl, whisking to combine.
Add to carrots along with sunflower seeds and scallions.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add other ingredients; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with grated cheese, sour cream, black olives and Doritos chips to taste.

title: old fashion sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into an uncooked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° until knife inserted into center of pie comes out clean.

title: chocolate raisin squares
directions: Melt chocolate pieces with peanut butter.
Stir in marshmallows and raisins.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares.

title: ranch burgers
directions: Add salad dressing mix to ground beef.
Mix well and form into patties.
Cook on grill and enjoy.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger; add remaining ingredients and cook.

title: smitty cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar in bowl.
Cut in shortening like for pie crust.
Beat egg yolks with vanilla; add to mixture and blend well.
Press into two ungreased 8-inch square pans, about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly; spread with jam.
Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Cover jam and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.
Makes about 36.

title: instant pudding cake
directions: Put all together; mix well.
Grease tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven until done, almost 1 hour.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Take hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and egg and mix all together.
Shape into 4 to 6 mini meat loaf patties.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening together.
Add sugar gradually, continuing until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg.
Sift flour and soda together.
Mix well.
Drop mixture by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Press down with tines of fork. Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Good for holidays.

title: carrot thyme soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the stock and the carrots.
Bring the stock to a boil.
Simmer the carrots, covered for 20 minutes or until they are tender.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cut each potato into 8 wedges lengthwise.
Arrange, peel side down, in a shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together and all Ranch dressing before serving with salt and pepper to taste.

title: berry good cocktails
directions: In a 12 ounce glass, first pour in the 2 shots, then put in jello popsicle, then pour in drink box, then add 7-Up or Sprite! Stir well and enjoy!

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, egg, 3/4 cup Rice Krispies, salt, pepper and onion; mix well.
Mix together sugar, catsup, nutmeg and mustard. Add half and 2/3 of this to meat mixture; mix well.
Shape into loaf and place in pan (9 x 5-inch pan).
Top with remaining sauce and cereal.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot wild turkey salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: harvest bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk in a large bowl and let stand 5 minutes.
Add 2 2/3 cups bread flour and next 7 ingredients, stirring until a soft dough forms.

title: filled potato dumplings
directions: Combine first 5 dry ingredients; mix lightly. Add creamed butter and onion. Add beaten eggs and mix well. Using an ice cream scoop, form mixture into balls around 4 or 5 small toasted croutons.
Place onto floured pan. Bring water or broth to a boil. Drop dumpling in to cook about 10 minutes or until they float. Serve. Sprinkle with browned butter and cracker crumbs.

title: butterscotch bundt cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam or Baker's Joy.
Preheat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan over low heat melt butter.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar until dissolved.
Add eggs, yogurt and vanilla.
In medium bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add butter mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir until just moistened.
Do not overmix!
Pour 1/2 batter into Bundt pan.
Sprinkle evenly with butterscotch chips.
Pour remaining batter in pan and smooth top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool on wire rack for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix rhubarb and 3 tablespoons flour well with 1 cup sugar. Put in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: no cook divinity candy
directions: Mix together the frosting mix (dry), corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water.
Beat on highest speed until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Blend powdered sugar in gradually.
Stir in nuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
When outside of candy feels firm, turn over.
Dry at least 12 hours.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen pieces.

title: tater skins
directions: Bake potatoes in microwave until done.
Cut in half, scoop out middle and set aside.
Fry skins in deep fat fryer until lightly brown.
Place on pizza pan.
Sprinkle on cheese and bacon bits. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Remove from oven; add dollop of sour cream and green onions.
Serve.

title: black-eyed pea chowder
directions: Saute bacon with celery, green pepper and onion. Add consomme, tomatoes, peas and chilies.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sandra's saucy appetizer franks(microwave)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until hot.
Stir in franks.
Cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes on High, stirring once.

title: pecan dream cookies
directions: Mix this up and make into balls the shape of a date.
Bake at 350° (you want them just light brown).
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot.
Do it again when cold.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Combine all cereals, etc.
Pour melted oleo over all.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 225° to 250°.
Pour garlic over gradually. Stir every 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook sugar, cranberries and water until berries pop open.
Add cherry jello.
Dissolve while still hot.
Let cool.
Add apples, pineapple, oranges and chopped nuts.
Mix and put in refrigerator to set.

title: chipper chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except chow mein noodles).
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Microwave power level: Medium (5) or Low (3).
Microwave time: 5 to 7 minutes total.

title: betty's icebox cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in pineapple juice (drained from pineapple) in top of double boiler.
Let congeal.
Add bananas, pineapple and whipped cream.
Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with whole vanilla wafers and pour filling in pan.
Sprinkle top with vanilla wafer crumbs.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with spray.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; set aside.
In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, cream the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in molasses and boiling water.
Stir in dry ingredients until moistened.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on rack.
Makes 16 servings.

title: ritzy pineapple
directions: Mix well the pineapple chunks, sugar, flour and cheese. Put in 2-quart baking dish.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix soup, milk, onion and parsley.
Dip chicken pieces into mixture, then into stuffing, coating well.
Should use all of stuffing.
Line shallow baking pan or dish with foil.
Spray with Pam.
Fold foil over chicken and drizzle butter over each piece. Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: syrup for cake or brownies
directions: Mix brown sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Mix in water.
Add butter.
Bring to boil about 2 minutes until thick.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Put in microwave; as heating, stir.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter and stir in.
Boil 1 more minute.
Remove and stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over popcorn, about 2 batches air popper popcorn.

title: yummy cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, oatmeal, baking soda and baking powder in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix the butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Slowly mix in dry ingredients.
When mixed, stir in chocolate chips.
Roll into balls (do not flatten).
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: spring herb dip
directions: In blender or food processor, blend all ingredients for 30 seconds or until smooth.
Cover; chill.
Serve with cut up vegetable.

title: festive sweet potato combo(ready to bake in just 7 easy minutes.)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 8 x 12-inch baking dish, layer sweet potatoes, 1/2 can French fried onions and the apple.
In small bowl, thoroughly combine pineapple, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon; pour pineapple mixture over sweet potato mixture.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sausage lasagna wraps
directions: Boil noodles until done.
Cut sausage in 3-inch pieces and then cut lengthwise, but not completely through.
Cut cheese to put inside each piece sausage.
Wrap pieces with noodles and put a toothpick in them.
Cover with sauce and grate cheese on top. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: steak with onion(zwiebelrostbraten)
directions: Slash fat edges of steaks to prevent curling.
Melt lard in skillet.
Add steaks and sear 2 to 3 minutes on each side until browned on the outside but still slightly red inside.
Season with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Keep warm.

title: egg noodles
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl.
Pour out onto floured board; knead and roll.
Divide in half and roll.
Cut in narrow strips. Shake out and drop in boiling broth.
Cut for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Melt margarine.
Spoon in flour.
Blend salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Add milk and put back on heat.
Stir contents until thickened.
Add onion and crab meat.
Put on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sherry and parsley before serving.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk and cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in water. Combine flour, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Cut in shortening until fine.
Add warm milk, eggs and yeast.
Beat until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or up to 1 week.
Roll out on floured board as biscuits.
Brush with melted butter; place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise for 3 hours.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 24.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Make sure you cook rice first, then cook broccoli.
Saute onion in butter.
Combine all ingredients together and mix.
Pour into dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered.

title: orange-pineapple sherbet
directions: Pour all ingredients into ice cream churn.
Follow normal churning instructions.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown onions,
beef and mushrooms; add soups and flour. Cook at 250° for 2 to 3 hours in oven.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Cut softened cream cheese into 24 squares.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix finely chopped celery and onion in bowl.
Add cooked and finely chopped chicken to this mixture.
Place one square of cheese and one spoonful of chicken mixture into crescent roll. Roll dough and pinch.
Put roll on cookie sheet and pour a little melted butter over it.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper and basil. Bake according to roll package.

title: disgustingly rich brownies(these are only for people who've been really good recently)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, then smear 9 x 13-inch baking pan with shortening.
Melt butter over low heat.
In mixing bowl, stir cocoa and sugar together.
Then stir in the melted butter.
Add the eggs and vanilla and stir again.
Now, add the flour and salt and mix just until smooth, not too much.
(Add nuts at this time if you want.)
Scrape mixture into greased pan and spread out in an even layer.
Bake in a 350° oven until the brownies just begin to pull away from the sides, about 20 to 30 minutes.
The hardest part: Let cool for a while before cutting.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix 1 package strawberry Kool-Aid with water.
Do not make full strength.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add Tang and 1/2 cup sugar. Freeze in 2 containers.
Should make enough for 2 bowls of punch. Chill ginger ale and pineapple juice.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix in order given and fry by tablespoonful on hot, greased griddle.

title: red devil franks
directions: Cook garlic and onions in margarine until tender.
Stir often. Add salt, pepper, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and chili sauce.
Continue heating until flavors are well blended.

title: artichoke pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Spread and flatten 2 cans of rolls on pizza pan or stone.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: yummy sundaes
directions: Blend 1 cup of love with 1/2 cup of kindness.
Alternately add in small portions:
1 cup appreciation and 3 cups of pleasant companionship into which has been sifted 2 teaspoons of deserving praise.
Flavor with 1 teaspoon of carefully chosen advice.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil, then add pumpkin, flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Pour in a jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or so.
Cool.

title: 100 dollar coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Bake into 2 round layers.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.
Slice layers to make 4 layers.

title: cheesy bagel bites
directions: Spread bagels with mustard.
Mix remaining ingredients. Spread to edges of bagels.
Broil bagels or bake at 550° until topping is bubbly, about 1 minute.
Cut each bagel into 6 pieces. Makes 36 appetizers.

title: tom's favorite chili
directions: Brown ground beef, turkey and onions.
Drain.
Add beans, tomatoes, sauce and chili powder (to taste).
Make rice.
Mix rice and chili in each bowl; top with Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Combine onion mixture in bowl with chopped chicken and chopped green chilies; set aside.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas, add other ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: grandma's molasses apple butter stack cake
directions: To melted butter, add molasses and milk; heat until warm (do not boil). Mix sugar and spices in bowl with 5 cups of the flour; use remaining flour to sprinkle on board and add to dough as needed.
Make a hole in the center of dry mixture of ingredients; gradually add warm mixture to center.
Add egg; mix until thick. Knead like bread dough to roll out on board.
Use small amount of mixture rolled out desired thickness of 1/4-inch. Cut out desired size to fit pan to bake.
Bake each layer at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Check after 10 minutes for doneness.

Makes 8 layers. Stack layers, spreading tops of each layer generously with apple butter. "Ice" sides of entire cake with apple butter. Let cake "set" for a few days after "icing" with the apple butter. It improves with age.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place ingredients in layers in 2-quart baking dish.
Layer the rice, corn and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water.
