Add green pepper and onion.
Layer ground beef.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour second can of tomato sauce and water.
Cover meat with bacon.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer, until bacon is crisped.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: german pizza
directions: Put oil in 10-inch skillet.
Spread half of the potato slices over bottom; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with a layer of half of the onion and half of the green pepper, seasoning with salt and pepper.
Arrange half of the meat on top.
Repeat layers of vegetables, reserving the remaining meat for garnish.
Cover; cook over low heat until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes. Break eggs into bowl and beat with fork; pour eggs evenly over potatoes.
Add meat, spoke-fashion.
Cover and cook until eggs are set, about 10 minutes.
Top with cheese; cover until cheese starts to melt, about 2 minutes.
Put parsley into center.
Cut in wedges to serve.
Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit, save pineapple juice.
Mix instant pudding in pineapple juice.
Combine all other ingredients and stir together. If salad seems too thick, add a little water.
Any fruit or fruit cocktail can be used.

title: kim's carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar. Add cinnamon and vanilla; mix well. Add oil, then flour and mix well. Stir in carrots, pineapple and nuts. Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 8 x 11 baking pan. Fill and bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool when done. Use Cream Cheese Icing when cooled.

title: cream cheese delight
directions: Mix together melted margarine and crushed graham crackers. Spread on bottom of pan, 9 x 13-inch.
With electric mixer, beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk until smooth.
Pour over cracker crust.
Spread 1 container of Cool Whip over cream mixture.
Next, spread 1 can of fruit pie filling over whipped cream.
Sprinkle with pecans, if desired.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: plain and simple cornbread
directions: Heat oiled 10-inch iron skillet.
Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Add milk, then unbeaten egg and mix well.
Heat oil and add.
Turn into hot skillet.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit shakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until well blended.
Chill before using.

title: peanutty cereal squares
directions: Butter a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large saucepan, melt butter, marshmallows and peanut butter over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Mix in cereal and peanuts until thoroughly coated.
Pat mixture into pan with buttered back of spoon. Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Cut into 2 1/4-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: blueberry cheesecake pie
directions: Meanwhile, wash and drain blueberries.
Combine blueberries, water, sugar and cornstarch.
Boil until clear, stirring constantly.
Add butter and mix until smooth.
Cool slightly. Pour over baked mixture.
Allow to cool.
Refrigerate.

title: eggless vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix 2 cups milk,
Eagle Brand milk, cool whip, vanilla and pudding mix together until well blended,
Add remaining 4 Cups milk.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: fruit salad dessert
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows and mix gently.
Fold in fruit salad.
Chill before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion and drain well.
Mix soup, milk and slightly beaten egg together.
Fold in squash and 1 cup of crumbs. Place in a greased casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Spot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach well; pat dry.
Pick stems off.
After it is dried, tear apart and place in serving bowl.
Slice onion across and pull apart (size like onion rings).
Combine all ingredients and top with about 6 ounces of the dressing; toss.
Enjoy.

title: whole wheat sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine first 10 ingredients in large bowl.
Blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into the measuring cup and level.
Stir in flour to mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in combined sugar and cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets 2-inches apart.
Flatten slightly.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until light golden brown.
Cookies will be soft in center.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, eggs, corn, bacon drippings, soda and salt. Pour light level of batter in bottom of 10 x 15-inch pan.
Next, add cheese.
Layer in meat and jalapenos.
Add remaining batter on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Can be halved and baked in 2 smaller pans.

title: easy blissful bean salad
directions: Fry and blot free of fat 1 pound bacon, cut into bits.
Do not use bacon bits.
Add to preceding mixture and mix well.

title: shrimp neptune
directions: Cook green noodles according to package directions and drain. In a skillet, saute raw shrimp in margarine for 5 minutes or until pink.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, mustard, chives, mushrooms and sherry.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, make layers beginning with green noodles, shrimp and sauce.
Then top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and serve as a dip for fresh vegetables.
Use raw carrots, celery, peppers, cauliflower, cucumbers, broccoli and tomatoes.

title: chicken rice dinner
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken pieces.
In a large skillet, over medium heat, brown the chicken in oil.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar. Combine eggs and oil; add to sifted ingredients.
Fold in drained strawberries.
Grease 2 large or 4 small loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Break up packages of noodles in small pieces.
(Do not use flavor packet.)
Saute seeds, noodles and almonds in butter or margarine until lightly browned; set aside.

title: chuck roast in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast in large piece of foil. Sprinkle with onion soup, spread cream of mushroom or cream of celery soup on top.
Wrap and seal the roast.
Bake until done. Remove and serve.

title: microwave pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Heat in microwave on High for 20 to 30 seconds or until melted.
Blend brown sugar with butter and pack evenly into bottom of dish.
Drain pineapple juice into glass measure.
Arrange pineapple slices over butter-brown sugar mixture.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, substituting pineapple juice for water.
Pour cake batter into dish, evenly distributing batter over entire surface.
Bake in microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until top springs back when lightly pressed with finger.
While hot, invert on serving plate.

title: reeses peanut butter cups
directions: Put chocolate chips, chocolate bars and 1/4 c. peanut butter in top of double boiler over HOT, not boiling water, stirring till smooth.
Use small muffin tin liners, or cut regular cupcake liners down to a 1 in. depth.
Spoon HALF of the chocolate mixture equally into the liners.
Melt the rest of the peanut butter over hot water, and spoon this equally over the chocolate layer.
Top with remaining chocolate.
Refrigerate to allow cups to set up before serving.

title: buffet stroganoff
directions: Saute beef in olive oil or butter until brown.
Add mushrooms, peppers and onions.
Saute.
Add beef stock (if stock is made from cubes, reduce salt to 1/2 teaspoon.) Simmer 15 minutes.
Mix flour and sour cream.
Add to beef mixture, stirring well to thicken. Simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Serve over hot buttered noodles. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: coleslaw
directions: Slice cabbage, green pepper and onion very fine.
Mix the sugar, salt, dry mustard and celery seed in saucepan.
Add oil and vinegar; let mixture come to a boil until sugar dissolves (about 3 minutes).
Pour over cabbage mixture; toss well.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: ham barbecue sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat in crock-pot or large pan.
Serve on sandwich rolls.
Makes 10 or 12 sandwiches.

title: spinach strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except spinach and strawberries.
Toss into spinach and strawberries just before serving.

title: plain soft custard
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Beat together slightly eggs, sugar and salt.
Add hot milk to egg mixture; mix thoroughly and return to top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until eggs coat spoon.
Add vanilla.

title: fudge
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over low heat until creamy.
Add peanut butter.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix flavored jello and unflavored gelatin.
Add boiling water; stir until completely dissolved.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan or larger.

title: apple harvest cookies
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients; add shortening, sugar, egg and water.
Beat until thoroughly mixed; stir in raw apples, oats and raisins.
Mixture will be stiff.
Make balls of dough, size of a large walnut and roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons of cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
To make drop cookies, add an extra egg.

title: lemon-strawberry punch
directions: Add and mix lemonade and strawberries.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice.

title: slow-cooker meal chicken barley soup
directions: Before lunch, place all the ingredients into slow cooker. Cover.
Cook on slow until dinner time.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Roll by hand into small balls about 3/4 inch in diameter.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot. Repeat when cool. Makes three dozen.
These freeze very nicely.

title: crab imperial
directions: Cook butter, flour, salt, pepper, mustard and milk
in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Add green pepper and crabmeat to mixture and toss.
Pour in baking dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake until golden brown on top at 325°.

title: april's chicken and rice
directions: Mix equal amounts of rice and chicken broth, then add about 2/3 can of water and another 1/4 can of rice.
Salt to taste; add 1 tablespoon of butter.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Add chicken; microwave on High for another 3 to 4 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Add walnuts last.
Grease 2 bread pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lo-cal strawberry cream cups
directions: Slice strawberries; break up angel food into bite size pieces. Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into dessert cups and refrigerate overnight.
"Wonderful lo-cal dessert!"

title: nutmeg flats
directions: In large bowl of mixer, cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add egg yolk and beat well.
Stir in flour and nutmeg.
With lightly floured fingertips, spread evenly in 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat egg white slightly and brush over top.
Bake in preheated 275° oven until rich golden color, about 1 hour. While hot, cut in 2 x 3/4-inch bars; remove to racks to cool. Makes about 96.

title: eula mae westbrook's frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain
fruit.
Soak
gelatin
in lemon juice, then dissolve over hot water.
Blend cream cheese with mayonnaise and salt. Stir
in
gelatin.	Whip
the cream until stiff, adding sugar gradually.	Fold
in
cheese
mixture,
nuts and fruit. Pour
into baking
pan
lined with wax paper and freeze for 4 hours
in
top of refrigerator.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine flour and Crisco; mix well with fork.
Add salt and sugar and mix.
After well blended, mix into a ball and refrigerate about 30 minutes.
On lightly floured board, roll the pastry to an 11-inch circle, rolling with light strokes from center to edge. Fold pastry in half; with fold in center, carefully transfer to a 9-inch pie plate.
Unfold; fit into a pie plate, pressing gently toward the center.
Fold edge of crust under; press into an upright rim.
Crimp edge.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Preheat oven to 450°. Prick entire surface evenly with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool on rack.
Makes pastry for one-crust pie.

title: jean goodwin's apple pie and crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Put into bowl or plastic bag and refrigerate until ready to use.
Use 1 cup for 1 pie crust.
Add cold water to make correct consistency.
For 2 pie crusts, use 1 3/4 to 2 cups.

title: apricot squares
directions: Sift
together
first 4 ingredients; cut in shortening. Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Blend well into dough.
Roll half of dough and put in large pan.
Spread with filling.
Top with rest of dough.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in margarine; add water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling and cubes dissolve.
Add noodles and boil, uncovered, 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli, garlic powder and chicken. Add cubed cheese and cook until melted, but do not boil.
Add milk and cook until hot.

title: cranberry-pineapple relish
directions: For the liquid use juice from pineapple and enough water to make 2 cups.
Combine with sugar and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add cranberries; bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes. Add pineapple, raisins, orange peel and pulp.
Cook about 10 minutes or until thick.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Toss lightly and turn into casserole.
Top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
If wanted, reheat for 10 minutes.

title: tabbouleh salad
directions: Combine bulgur wheat, boiling water and salt in bowl.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Add garlic, lemon and oil; mix and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Just before serving, add the rest of ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: judy's cheese ball
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Mix whipped topping and Eagle Brand milk together.
Add all other ingredients; mix together.
Refrigerate and enjoy.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Simmer 4 cups water, celery, onion and bouillon for 20 minutes.
Add carrots, potatoes, frozen vegetables and simmer for 40 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup and cheese, stir frequently to prevent cheese from burning or sticking.
Add additional water or bouillon as needed for taste.

title: confetti coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, with wire whisk or fork, mix olive oil, vinegar, mustard, sugar, celery seed, salt and black pepper.
Set dressing aside.

title: banana nut bread(no egg)
directions: Blend shortening and sugar until creamy. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture. Add mashed bananas, lemon juice and nuts. Bake in well-greased 2 small loaf pans or 1 regular size bread pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine milk, egg yolks and lemon juice. Stir well. Pour in pie crust and bake for 10 minutes or until pie is thick. Top with cool whip.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix peas, cheese, onion, carrot and bacon together.
Drop Miracle Whip by teaspoonful onto mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar. Drizzle with vinegar.
Chill well.
Mix right before serving.

title: california rangers
directions: Cream butter; add sugars.
Gradually add milk, vanilla and eggs. Then add flour, salt, soda and baking powder, then add oats, coconut and corn flakes.
Form in small balls.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Combine
crumbs
and
other ingredients.
Pour into pie plate and press to form shell.
Bake 5 minutes at 275°.

title: veggie pizza bites
directions: Spread rectangles of crescent roll dough over bottom of cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until rich golden brown.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix.
Spread evenly over cooled crust.
Chop fresh vegetables fairly small.
Sprinkle generously over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over the top. Refrigerate.
Cut and serve.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Save 3 or 4 onion rings for topping.
Place the rest in the bottom of a baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Cover onions with ground beef; break lightly with a fork, but do not pack down.
Sprinkle with salt, basil and oregano; top with saved onion rings.

title: slovenian harvest chili
directions: Cook sausages in boiling water until done, 10 to 12 minutes. Slice thin.
In heavy 5 to 6-quart Dutch oven or stockpot, brown sausage slices and ground beef, stirring to separate beef into small pieces.
Remove meats from pan.
Saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in remaining fat in pan.
Spoon off excess fat. Return meats to pan.
Add tomatoes, barbecue sauce, kidney beans and seasonings.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve topped with cheese.
Makes 16 cups.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine and cook the first 6 ingredients until thick.
Then layer the mixture in between bananas and wafers.

title: grandma quinn's raisin cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large kettle; boil for 3 minutes.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Dissolve baking soda in coffee.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
(Recipe can be doubled or tripled and baked in loaf pans for Christmas gifts, etc.)

title: german chocolate no-cook fudge
directions: Butter 8 inch square pan; set aside. Melt chocolate and chips in heavy saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in condensed milk, chopped pecans and vanilla until combined. Spread in prepared pan. Arrange pecan halves on fudge. Score fudge into squares with knife. Refrigerate until firm. Cut into squares. Store in refrigerator. Bring to room temperature before serving. Makes about 2 pounds.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice the day before and refrigerate overnight.
Heat oil in deep skillet or wok.
Cook rice in it, stirring steadily and pressing out lumps, until lightly browned.
Add meat, onions, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Make a hollow in the center and pour eggs into it.
Stir until they begin to set. Mix into rice mixture.
Blend in parsley and soy sauce.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender and browned, turning potatoes occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle cheese over top and let melt.
Serve.

title: piccalilli
directions: Chop tomatoes, cucumbers, peppers and onions to relish consistency.
Mix with salt and set aside for 12 hours.
Drain well and press out extra liquid.
Heat vinegar, sugar and spices. Add chopped vegetables and bring to a boil.
Pack into jars and seal at once.

title: deluxe potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour into potatoes, etc., in large mixing bowl.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cheesy chili success
directions: Prepare Success rice according to package directions; drain. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Stir to blend well.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Garnish with red bell pepper or tomato slices, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: farm cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add the flour, baking powder, soda and remaining ingredients.
Mix well and either drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet or make into small balls in the palms of your hands and put onto the greased sheet.
Press with a fork.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes
6 dozen.

title: light and creamy scallops and pasta
directions: In a wide nonstick frying pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter or margarine over medium heat.
Add scallops and cook, stirring just until opaque (1 or 2 minutes).
Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix water and soup mix together, then mix with meat and eggs. Mix remaining ingredients together.
Put half mixture in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown meatballs in skillet.
Lay on top of mixture, pour remaining mixture over meatballs.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, covered with foil.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla. Bring to a full boil and cook for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and beat, adding vanilla. Start spreading on cake before it seems thick enough. If it gets too stiff, add a little cream or milk. Makes enough for 3 layer cake.

title: charcoal broiled chicken
directions: Mix marinade and pour over chicken.
Marinate at least 12 hours.
More is better.
Grill chicken, basting with marinade, if you like.

title: barbecue turkey
directions: Combine all ingredients, except turkey; bring to a boil.
Add breast.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours, turning often, pulling turkey from bones with a fork as it cooks.
Remove bones and serve.

title: flank steak
directions: Pierce steak on both sides.
Place in covered dish or bowl and marinate overnight.
Charcoal on grill about 5 minutes on each side.

title: cheesy cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Set aside to cool. Mix the cream cheese with pineapple juice, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Chill until set.
After set, pour a little warm water over mold to empty.

title: pineapple "julius"
directions: Place in blender and process 30 seconds.
Makes 2 large servings.
May add 1 1/2 cups fresh chilled fruit.

title: taco casserole
directions: Fry ground round until brown; drain.
Add pinto beans and jalapeno pinto beans.
Stir in taco sauce and taco seasoning mix. Pour into a large baking dish or pan.
Cover with grated cheese. Put crushed taco nacho cheese on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve over chopped lettuce and tomato.

title: filled cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll until thin.
Cut cookies.
Place on tin and put filling between 2 cookies.
Bake at 350 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad(makes 12 muffin cups)
directions: Blend together all ingredients and place in muffin papers in muffin tins.
Freeze.
After frozen, take from tins and place in Ziploc bags.
Serve as a special dessert or on a lettuce leaf, garnished with cherries.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a large pot, melt butter.
Add onion, garlic and chicken. Brown chicken on both sides.
Add milk, parsley flakes and soup. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in saucepan. Heat over medium heat until mixture reaches soft-ball stage. Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients; stir until completely mixed. Pour in greased (margarine) square pan. Put in refrigerator. Cut into squares.

title: quick cake
directions: Mix the ingredients in a bowl.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: low-fat cold rice salad
directions: Prepare rice and cool in refrigerator.
Prepare sun-dried tomatoes as directed.
Chop cheese, tomatoes and onion and mix with rice.
Add enough dressing to moisten and hold ingredients together.
Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal and sour cherry soda bread(makes 1 loaf, 8 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease large baking sheet.
In large bowl, with fork, combine whole-wheat and all-purpose flours, 1/2 cup oats, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cherries and caraway seed, if desired.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Bake sesame seed and almonds for 5 minutes at 350°.

title: miniature mounds
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter.
Mix coconut, nuts, Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and food coloring.
Pour butter in.
Mix in powdered sugar until in firm ball.
Pinch off pieces and set in refrigerator to chill.

title: our favorite tuna noodle casserole
directions: In a saucepan, blend 1 can cream of celery soup and 1/2 cup milk, then add 4 ozs. sharp cheddar cheese, shredded, (1 cup). Stir until cheese melts on low heat.
Pour into the noodle mixture and turn into a 2 quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs (we use the Italian style).
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage balls
directions: Boil head of cabbage in large pot until leaves feel limp. Remove and drain; cut off leaves individually.
Mix together beef, sausage, onion and rice.
Put small amount in middle of cabbage leaf and roll.
Secure with toothpick.
Place cabbage balls in deep pot and cover with tomato juice.
Put lid on pot and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Don't forget to remove toothpick before eating!!

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzel crumbs with sugar and butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan; press firmly.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.

title: poor boy cake
directions: Mix together.
Beat well.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fried rice
directions: In a wok, saute vegetables and salami in oil until vegetables are tender.
Add rice; mix well and push to side of wok or pan. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in wok or pan and scramble 3 eggs until set.
Mix together all ingredients.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Bake cake as usual.
Slice layers into two layers each, making four layers.
Crush Heath bars and mix into Cool Whip.
Frost with Cool Whip mixture between layers, tops and sides.
Store in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: In mixer bowl, combine egg yolks, cheese, mayonnaise, bouillon and horseradish.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon or pipe into reserved whites.
Garnish with olives.
Refrigerate.

title: "onion rings"
directions: Pour buttermilk into a shallow pan.
Add onion rings and allow to soak 30 minutes.
Combine egg, salt, baking powder, water, flour, oil, lemon juice and pepper; stir until smooth.

title: broccoli bow ties
directions: Prepare noodles.
Steam broccoli for 5 minutes.
Combine hot noodles, broccoli and olive oil.
Toss well.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, 1/2 cup of sugar at a time; add eggs, one at a time and mix in well.
Combine flour and salt; add to butter mixture, a small amount at a time.
Stir in buttermilk and then pour butter into unbaked shell and bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours (until pie is a golden brown).
Sprinkle the pecan halves on top of pie and let it cool thoroughly.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Put cooked zucchini in bowl with 2 tablespoons lemon juice; set aside.
Mix all ingredients together with zucchini.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: brownies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured pan for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly and cut into squares.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and brown.
Cook noodles; add 1 Tbsp. salt and 1 Tbsp. oil to water.
Put cooked noodles on bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Layer cottage cheese, meat mixture, mozzarella cheese, parmesan; repeat, ending with parmesan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Layer in crock-pot the stew meat, onion soup mix, potatoes, carrots, cream of celery soup, cream of mushroom soup, tomato sauce and bay leaf (optional).
Do not stir.
Cook 6 hours on low.

title: pasta and creamed prosciutto sauce
directions: Cut Prosciutto into cubes, smaller than 1/2 inch.
Melt the butter in a large casserole over low heat.	Add Prosciutto and saute lightly for 1
minute.
At the same time bring a pot of cold water to a boil.
Add salt and 1 teaspoon olive oil to water, then add pasta
and cook to desired texture.
Drain the pasta
and
add it	to
the
casserole
with
the
Prosciutto. Immediately pour the cream
over
the
pasta
and
season with salt,
pepper and nutmeg.
Gently
mix
all
the
ingredients together,
then add the
cheese.
Mix
again;
transfer
to
a warmed serving dish and serve immediately.	Serves 8.

title: reunion salad
directions: Bake cornbread mixes according to directions on package.
Cool and crumble into a large bowl.
Add corn, mayonnaise, tomatoes, peppers, onions, cheese and seasoning to suit your taste.
It's delicious!

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Place hash browns in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together, mix with hash browns, add Cheddar cheese and mix.
Pour melted butter over top; crush cornflakes into fine crumbs.
Sprinkle over entire top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: butter pecan cream cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Stir together margarine, 1 egg and cake mix.
Then press into bottom of pan, leaving slight edge all around.
Then blend together 2 eggs, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Pour over first mixture.
Then sprinkle with pecan chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Don't use butter brickle cake mix.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix the butter, sugar, milk, and cocoa. Boil for 2 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper to cool and harden.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Combine buttermilk and soda and let stand for 5 minutes.
Pour into deep 4-quart, stainless steel pot.
Add sugar and syrup. Slowly bring to boil, stirring constantly, and bring to soft ball stage.
Remove pan from heat and let cool slightly.
Beat with wooden spoon (you may use a hand mixer, but be careful as it will set up quickly) until smooth and creamy and reaches butterscotch color.
With spoon, swirl into mounds on wax paper.
Let cool, then store in airtight container.

title: no bake dirt cake
directions: Put 1/2 of Oreos in bottom of deep cake pan.
Then mix other ingredients together and pour on cookies.
Put the rest on top.

title: poor man's cobbler
directions: Place melted butter in deep dish.
Mix together other ingredients.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Empty one can of fruit over all.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple squares
directions: In large bowl, mix oleo into dry cake mix.
Set aside 1 cup. Press
remaining
mixture
into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spoon pie
filling
over
mixture.
In
small
bowl,
combine reserved cake mixture and coconut.
Sprinkle over pie filling. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Completely thaw spinach.
Squeeze dry.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Ranch dressing together.
Add spinach.
Chop water chestnuts fine.
Add to mixture.
Refrigerate.
Serve with cut-up veggie and cracks.
Low in calorie; high in flavor.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar.
Stir in 2/3 cup pumpkin and teaspoon of lemon juice.
Stir together 3/4 cup flour, 2 teaspoons of cinnamon, 1 teaspoon of ginger and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Fold into pumpkin.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up cake and towel together.
Cool. Unroll for filling.
Trim around edge.
Beat until smooth the powdered sugar, cream cheese, margarine and vanilla.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll up and chill well.
Slice and eat.

title: apricot pound cake
directions: Mix and bring to boiling point.

title: dream pudding(serves about 10)
directions: Drain pineapple.
Soften cream cheese with a little of the juice.
Whip up Dream Whip according to the directions.
Whip up soft swirl.
Mix with cream cheese.
Beat until well mixed.
Add pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: potluck vegetable casserole
directions: Pour butter over bread crumbs.
Cook 30 minutes at 375°.

title: paximadia greek toasts
directions: Place oil and sugar in bowl and blend well.
Add one egg at a time and beat well.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix until batter is smooth (batter is very soft).
Divide in five and place in greased and floured bread pans.
Brush with milk.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pans and slice while hot, then let cool for 10 minutes.
Place flat on cookie sheet and return to oven until lightly golden in color (about 10 minutes).

title: erica's apples
directions: Put apples in a mixing bowl; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve in a dessert cup.

title: cream cheese candy
directions: Cream sugar and cheese. Divide into 3 parts.
Put peppermint and green color in 1 section.
Put butter and 1/2 teaspoon yellow in 1 section.
Put lemon and 1/2 teaspoon yellow in last section. Press into molds; air dry 2 hours.

title: booga hollow dump cake
directions: Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan the pineapple chunks. Sprinkle over this the coconut.
Dump and smooth over this the cake mix.
Dot entire surface with butter pieces.
Do not mix! Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until light brown; cool and cut into squares.

title: south dakota white chili
directions: Place beans in a heavy large pot.
Add enough cold water to cover by at least 3 inches and soak overnight.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Put evaporated milk, chocolate pieces and salt in a 1-quart saucepan.
Stir over low heat until chocolate melts completely and mixture thickens.
Take off heat.
Stir in marshmallows until melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Spoon half of ice cream into wafer shell.
Cover with half of chocolate mixture.
Repeat with rest of ice cream and chocolate.
Top with pecans.
Freeze about 5 hours.

title: hot and spicy punch
directions: Prepare tea and remove bags.
Add other ingredients; simmer.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk together; bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix until oats are covered with chocolate mixture.
Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Work butter and cheese together with hands or wooden spoon. Add flour and mix, then add Rice Krispies.
Roll in marble size balls and press with a fork.
Sprinkle with red pepper or paprika. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Cook bacon crisp; crumble. Combine 2/3 cup bacon drippings with next 5 ingredients.
Heat and stir until thickened.
Add potatoes, onion and bacon; toss, heat through (makes 5 pounds).

title: cheesy spaghetti
directions: Makes 6 servings.
Brown chuck and onion in frying pan. Drain.
Add sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Break spaghetti into thirds.
Cook according to package.
Rinse and drain.
Mix with sauce.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt. Slowly add milk and water.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until thick.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and Parmesan cheese. Stir until melted.
Spread 1/2 spaghetti mixture in the bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon all of cheese sauce over this and add remaining spaghetti sauce on top, then add 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hollywood dunk
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients well and fold into whipped cream.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and dry gelatin mix to this. Add cooking oil and milk. Add eggs, one at a time, beating on medium speed with electric mixer. Fold in strawberries and pecans. Pour into a lightly greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 oblong pan (or 3 or 4 round cake pans). Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes to 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook all ingredients except milk until tender.
Drain, saving liquid.
Blend potato mixture until smooth.
Return to pot, adding the broth you saved and the milk.
Stir well.
Heat on low just until mixture is hot.
Serves 6 people.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef, onion, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
In casserole dish, layer ground beef mixture, cheese and biscuits until all ingredients are gone.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix strawberries, jello, pineapple, bananas and apples.
Let set and chill.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and nuts.
Spread over chilled jello mixture.

title: strawberry salad mold
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add thawed strawberries; add strained pineapple and stir.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into mold or Pyrex dish.
Chill until thick.
Spread sour cream evenly over jello; add remaining jello mixture.
Chill overnight until set.

title: nettie's fruit cake
directions: Beat 3 eggs. Blend with sugar.
Add flour and blend. Add fruit, peeled and cubed.
Butter 9-inch square pan and line with buttered wax paper.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: unbelievable meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch and cold water.
Stir in boiling water and cook to thicken.
Cool.
Add lemon juice to egg whites and beat to soft peaks.
Add sugar gradually.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pretzel-strawberry salad
directions: Melt margarine and
mix
with
crushed pretzels.
Press down as crust in 9
x 13-inch ovenproof dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: heringssalat rheinischer art(rhineland herring salad)
directions: A line shack on the mountain.
I cooked a Betty Crocker apple pie mix.
As I took it from the oven, it ended upside down on the hard dirt floor.

Harvey Robinson was there, he dearly loved pie. He looked at that pie on the floor and said, "I could just cry!" He and my nephew Preston Brunst got forks and sat down on the hard dirt floor and proceeded to eat what they could of the pie before getting to the dirt.

title: fruit bread
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar; add eggs and mix well. Mash the bananas, then add to the butter.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add to the butter and blend well.
Stir in the nuts, cherries and chocolate chips.
Pour into 2 large or 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour and flavoring.
Beat until smooth, then add flour; beat until smooth.
Add flavoring and beat.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: waldorf imperial salad
directions: Use large mixing bowl. Wash apples and dice, unpeeled. Combine with celery, raisins, pecans, cherries, grapes and salt. Toss with Mayonnaise. Garnish with red cherries and chill. Makes 9 cups.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Add noodles and chicken over heat.
Stir occasionally.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: date-nut surprises
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal, pecans and vanilla.
Let mixture cool to touch.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cool on wire racks.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: sunshine baked eggs
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain and discard all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon.
In a large bowl, lightly beat eggs; add bacon and drippings, cottage cheese, pineapple and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
If desired, garnish with parsley.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Slice pepperoni into bits and strips.
Heat and then drain on paper towels.
Add to salads, both tossed and pasta salads.
Good to use hot or cold.
May keep in jar in refrigerator.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except chips. Spoon into buttered 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with crumbled potato chips.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Heat almonds in a moderate oven until light brown.
Cut fruit and nuts in small pieces.
Melt butter and add sugar.
Mix together until blended.
Add beaten eggs.
Dredge fruit and nuts in half of flour.
Sift together the other half of flour, baking powder and cream of tartar.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Add fruit and nuts to batter.
Line pan with wax paper.
Fill pan 3/4 full of cake batter.
Bake 4 hours in a 300° oven or cook in pressure cooker at 10 for 45 minutes, then at 15 for 30 minutes.
Put cake in slow oven for 15 minutes to dry out. Put 7 to 8 cups of water in pressure cooker for that period of time.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Brush chicken with 1/4 cup butter.
Place flour and chicken in a plastic bag.
Shake to coat chicken. Arrange chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cook (boiling) all ingredients until begins to thicken.
Strain and run pulp through blender and pour back with juice.
Continue cooking until thickness you prefer.
Fill jars, seal and hot water bath for 35 minutes.

title: cheese and sausage pie
directions: Prepare 2 (9-inch) pie crusts according to package directions, only change baking time to 8 minutes at 450°.
Fry sausage pieces until done.
Reserve 3 tablespoons fat to cook onion and green pepper.
Set sausage aside.
Cook eggplant and zucchini in salted boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Set aside.
Cook onion and green pepper until soft.
Add flour and stir.
Mix in salt, pepper, oregano or thyme, pimento and soup.
Heat and stir until bubbles form and remove from heat.
Stir beaten eggs slowly into mixture.
Fold in cheese, sausage and vegetables.
Pour into pie crusts and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies and freezes well.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, if needed.
Mix sugar or syrup and butter with flour until crumbly. Spread over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 375°.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Mix all together in large pan.
Bring to boil and boil for 20 minutes.
Stir frequently to keep from sticking.
Pour into very hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 4 1/2 pints.

title: sharp potato bake
directions: Brown 1/2 pound bacon.
Crumble and set aside.
Cook 8 to 12 potatoes.
Dice these after they have cooled.
Add salad dressing, onion, grated sharp cheese and crumbled bacon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl, drop on greased cookie sheet, bake at 350° until desired brownness.

title: fried turkey breast
directions: Fillet the breast meat away from the bone and cut into thin 1/4-inch slices.
Dip the slices in a mixture of egg and milk. Roll in the bread crumbs.
In a heavy skillet, heat the oil to a medium-high temperature.
Fry the slices for 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
After each piece is cooked, place on paper towel covered platter.
Keep platter warm in the oven at 150°.

title: fried bananas
directions: Peel and slice bananas 1/4 inch thick. Pour milk in bowl. Pour sugar and cinnamon in another bowl, stir. Dip bananas in milk, then dip in sugar mixture. Fry at 350 degrees for about 2 minutes.

title: healthy cheese danish
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except toast; place on toasted bread.
Put under broiler for 1 or 2 minutes.
Toast until heated.
Serves 1.

title: dandelion greens with corn and red peppers
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan over medium heat. Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, until dandelion greens wilt.
Serves 2.

title: anderson's pleasure
directions: Mix all thoroughly.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Beat eggs with mixer until very light.
Gradually add sugar; continue to beat.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture.
Heat butter and milk until butter is melted; do not boil.
Add to batter all at once, stirring well. Add flavoring.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake for 25 minutes. Turn cake out immediately.
Cool on racks.

title: chocolate peanut butter cake
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Add eggs, water, cocoa and buttermilk.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder and sugar. Add cooked ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce up into medium-size pieces (about 12 cups). Place lettuce in a 3-quart bowl.
Fry bacon over medium heat until crisp.
Remove bacon with a slotted spoon; sprinkle over lettuce. In same skillet bacon was fried, add sugar, vinegar and salt to bacon grease.
Heat to boiling; immediately pour over lettuce. Toss just until lettuce is wilted.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Make ahead, either early in the day or a day before and refrigerate until used.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Fry meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: pound cake, my mother's recipe, years and years ago
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until well blended.
Add flour; beat well.
Mix in lemon flavor.
Put in tube pan; place in cold oven.
Set temperature at 325° and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: corn squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender; drain. Mix with cream-style corn. Pour into 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese and bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted and bubbly. Serves 8.

title: batter white bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water.
Let stand, then stir.
Add 3 1/4 cups flour, sugar, salt and shortening.
Beat well; add rest of flour.
Cover and let rise until doubled (45 minutes).
Stir down; put into 2 greased bread pans.
Let rise until double (20 minutes or more).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Rub with margarine to keep crust soft.

title: magic fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of baking dish.
Mix milk, sugar, flour and baking powder and pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit over batter.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle additional sugar over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Fruit will sink and batter will rise.
Add a little cinnamon to peaches or apples and almond flavor to cherries.

title: fried bass
directions: Mix salt, lemon pepper seasoning, lemon juice and mustard together.
Coat fillets with mixture; let stand 1 to 2 hours. Roll in corn meal and fry in hot, deep fat.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Keep all cans in the refrigerator to keep cool until you make it.

title: deli salad
directions: Add all ingredients to cooled shells. Toss well. Mix Italian dressing per package and pour over salad. Toss well. Let stand overnight.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Spray skillet with canola oil and add juice, teriyaki and chicken to iron skillet. Bring to a boil; cover. Cook until 1/4-inch of liquid is in bottom of skillet. Add 2 tablespoons honey; turn frequently until brown in color. Cook 25 to 30 minutes. Do not cook on low temperature.

title: "philly" miracle whip dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayo, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix ingredients, adding egg whites last.
Bake in oblong pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pheasant supreme
directions: Brown pheasants in skillet in small amount of butter.
Place browned pieces in a 2-quart ovenproof casserole dish.
In saucepan, combine soup, mushrooms and almonds.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over pheasant.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
May substitute chicken.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Allow to cool and cut into bars.

title: chicken dorito casserole
directions: Mix cream of mushroom, cream of chicken, and RoTel in a bowl. Boil your chicken and separate after boiled.
For best results, use a glass casserole dish to bake.
Place 1/2 bag of Doritos on bottom of pan.
Place 1/2 of chicken on top of Doritos, then pour 1/2 of cream mixture on top of chicken.
Add 4 slices of cheese on top of your layer.
Repeat for second layer.
Bake at 350° until heated all of the way through the casserole and the cheese is melted.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Cut in 2/3 cup margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 3/4-inch thick; cut with a biscuit cutter. Place biscuits on a lightly greased baking sheet; brush tops with melted margarine.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Yields 15 biscuits.

title: ham rolls with cheese sauce
directions: Add butter and mustard to ground ham and mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening and mix in well with fork.
Add liquid to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and toss lightly until outside looks smooth.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick in sheet 12-inches long and 10-inches wide. Spread with ham mixture.
Roll up lengthwise like a jelly roll and cut into slices 1 1/2-inches thick.
Flatten each slice down to 1-inch thick and place in greased pan.
Bake in hot oven, 475°, about 14 minutes.
Makes 8 rolls.
Serve with Cheese Sauce.

title: diet cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Blend in flour and baking powder.
Add artificial sweetener, vanilla and liquid (milk, juice or coffee). Mix well.
Sprinkle cinnamon over dough and knead.	Dough will have streaked appearance.
Shape dough into balls, about 1/2-inch, and place on greased cookie sheet.	Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until edges are brown.

title: becky's chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil hen in enough water to make 2 quarts of stock.
Saute onions, peppers, celery and garlic in butter.
Add 1 quart stock and tomatoes and simmer together.
Bone chicken and cut into rather large pieces.
Mix with sauce and put in casserole.
Add spaghetti which has been cooked in chicken stock (drain before adding), mixing well with chicken and sauce.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven; sprinkle with grated cheese and bake 20 minutes more. Serves 8 to 10.

title: orzo casserole
directions: Cook Orzo according to package directions; rinse, drain and set aside.
Saute onions and peppers in butter until tender; sprinkle in two envelopes beef broth.
In large casserole, combine onion, peppers and one can Durkee onion rings, along with the Orzo.
Top casserole mixture with the other can Durkee onion rings and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: honey-pecan pork chops
directions: Pound each chop to 1/4-inch thickness.
Dredge chops in flour, shaking off excess.
Heat one tablespoon butter in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add chops and brown on both sides, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir together remaining butter, honey and pecans.
Add to skillet; stir gently.
Cover and simmer gently for 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove pork chops to serving platter and pour the sauce over them.
Preparation time: 20 minutes.

title: orange mint punch
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water; add sugar.
Stir well and cool.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Makes 25 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill and serve.
This is good.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage and drain.
Roll out or press 1 can crescent rolls into a greased 9x13 casserole dish and press out holes to	form a solid crust.
Mix sausage with cream cheese and spread mixture over crescent rolls.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese on top and put a second layer of crescent rolls over cheese.
Press out holes and folds.
Bake for approximately 15 minutes or until rolls are browned.
Serves 8.

title: oven-baked chicken
directions: Wash cut up chicken and season as you usually do. Dip and coat each piece in flour.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Dot chicken pieces with 1/2 to 1 teaspoon of butter.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with your favorite side dishes.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots in water for 30 minutes.
Drain and chop.
Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs and add alternately with orange juice.
Add in the following order:
dry ingredients, nuts, apricots and orange rind.
Pour into lined loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla. Sift together salt, baking powder and flour.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat well.
Bake in a greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Serve warm with lemon sauce.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 2 hours.

title: green bean bake
directions: Saute onions
in margarine until tender. Combine beans, onions and soup
and put into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.	Top with asparagus.	Sprinkle
with	cheese,
then top with potato chips. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: k~y pie
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Cool and serve.

title: crab meat mold
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Remove tendons from crab meat and break apart.
Combine crab meat, cheese and remaining ingredients.
Lightly brush 1 1/2-quart mold with salad oil and press crab mixture into it.

title: round steak in crock-pot
directions: Stir together.
Add raw meat.
Cook 3 1/2 to 4 hours on high. Cook 6 to 8 hours on low.

title: roasted red skin potato
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place potatoes in roasting pan; drizzle oil over potatoes along with salt, pepper and onion wedges and roast for 20 minutes.
Add rosemary and turn potatoes and onion. Continue roasting for another 20 minutes.
Place on platter and serve.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press crescent rolls on a greased cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Spread mix on crust, then top with your favorite grated vegetables, cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, tomatoes and cheese of your choice.
Cut and serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill well.
Great with all your fresh vegetables from the garden.
Also fresh mushrooms, broccoli and cauliflower.

title: chocolate sheet crackers
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar, bring to a boil for 2 minutes. Place individual layer of crackers on two cookie sheets.
Pour and spread butter/brown sugar over the crackers.
Place in oven for 3/5 minutes at 450 degrees.
Take out; spread one bag of chips out on each cookie sheet.
They will melt.
After 5 minutes, spread melted chips around the cookie sheet to cover every cracker.
Add any topping of choice, sprinkles or sugar, etc.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Pull out and break off into pieces and serve.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar, salt and shortening to hot water.
Let cool. Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in warm water.
Add to hot water mixture.
Beat eggs.
Add to hot water mixture.
Add 4 cups flour and mix well.
Add other 4 cups flour, mix well again.
Place in well-greased bowl; cover with wax paper and damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator until mixture rises or until ready to use.
Work down; make into rolls and bake.
Mixture will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: sugar biscuits
directions: Brush tops of frozen biscuits with whipping cream; sprinkle evenly with sugar and cinnamon. Place biscuits on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: honey pumpkin pie
directions: Scald milk.
Mix other ingredients and all milk.
Pour into uncooked crust.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Reduce oven to 325° and bake about 35 minutes or until set.
This amount will make two 8 or 9-inch pieces.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add pineapple and mix well.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Melt butter and add cubed bread to butter and put on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Can be used for fruit or dessert. Also hot or cold.

title: crunchy beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Brown ground meat; drain. Combine all ingredients, except onion rings.
Pour into greased two casseroles.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and top with onion rings, then bake 5 minutes longer.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and flour.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell and bake 45 minutes in moderate oven (325° to 350°) or until lightly golden and set.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions; set aside.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.

title: tammy's lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain; add water, sauce and salt.
Mix cottage cheese with eggs until well blended.
Layer ingredients in lasagna pan in following order: meat, sauce, noodles, cottage cheese/egg mixture and Mozzarella.
Repeat preceding layers and add another layer of sauce, then the Parmesan.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, stirring 4 minutes. Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: in memory of fr. jack price potatoes
directions: Make large foil "boats" out of heavy aluminum foil or 2 sheets folded together.
Place about 1 tablespoon of oil on bottom.
Lay a row of sliced potatoes, green peppers and onion rings on top. Salt and pepper.
Add another row of sliced potatoes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Close foil tightly.
Place on hot charcoal grill for 7 to 10 minutes.
Flip boat over for another 4 to 5 minutes. Open foil; place on plate or eat at campfire when camping.

title: cream of wheat bread
directions: Stir gently.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: crawfish jambalaya
directions: Mix all ingredients in rice cooker pot.
Cook as you would cook rice.
As soon as bell rings, unplug rice cooker and leave covered 10 minutes to finish cooking.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon;
drain
and	crumble.
Add
onion and celery until transparent.
Add
juice
and
diced potato.
Cook for a few minutes,
but
not until potatoes are soft.
Mix the flour and melted butter with a small amount of liquid; add gradually to clams
and	potato mixture.
Bring to a boil, slowly adding rest of seasoning.
Stir well.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix together all the ingredients except cornflakes.
Bring to boil and add cornflakes.
Stir until blended and drop on wax paper.

title: parmesan onions
directions: Cut 12 (12-inch) squares of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Place an onion half, cut side up, in center of each. Dot each onion with butter; sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.
Wrap well; place on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender. Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: carrot and banana bread
directions: Combine oil and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon, then add to oil, sugar and eggs, alternately, with mashed bananas.
Stir in carrots and pecans.

title: miceli's cherry italian cookies
directions: Follow ingredients, then mix.
Put cookie dough on sheet. Cook at 375°.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add eggs; mixing well.
Add flour alternately with 7-Up.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 325° until toothpick inserted comes out clean (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Enjoy!

title: yum yum casserole
directions: In a 9 x 9 inch pyrex pan. Press ground meat into bottom of pan. Sprinkle onion on top. Add veggies and soup. Do not add water. Sprinkle cheese on top. Press down with fork. Spread tater tots all over the top. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry-rhubarb jam
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until rhubarb is cooked, 20 minutes. Add jello and Sure-Jell.
Stir up very good, then put in sterilized jars.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients and top with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: In Dutch oven or deep skillet, brown chicken in shortening. Remove.
In same skillet, saut onion.
Remove from heat; stir in cornstarch, salt and ginger.
Blend in water, consomm, mandarin oranges and jelly.
Cook while stirring until sauce is clear and thickened.
Add chicken and quartered orange pieces.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley and orange slices.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pineapple ruby punch
directions: Makes 25 cups.
May freeze in milk cartons to make slushy.

title: nacho supreme
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, brown meat.
Spoon off fat and mix in taco seasoning.
Add refried beans and simmer for 10 minutes.
In 4-quart dish, combine meat mixture, 1 cup of cheese, olives, green onions and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Spread remaining sour cream over the top and garnish with remaining cheese.
Serve over tortilla chips.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown hamburg and onion and set aside.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup, chili beans, enchilada sauce and green chilies.
Add hamburg to this mixture.
Cut 12 corn tortillas into quarters.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with tortillas and layer with hamburg and soup mixture alternately with tortillas ending with mixture.
Top with Longhorn cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over cottage cheese.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Can be served immediately.
Additional fruit can be added to compliment Jell-O flavor as mandarin oranges with orange Jell-O.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Place softened sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour liquids over the sherbet.
Let set about 20 minutes or until the sherbet is almost melted.
Then serve.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Mix together and press evenly into pan.
Sprinkle chips evenly over crumbs; then nuts and coconut.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: dandy's jello
directions: Mix and spread over salad.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in cup of boiling water.
Add cream cheese and beat with mixer; will have lumps.
Mix in rest of ingredients; add 7-Up.
Chill overnight.

title: eggs brunch
directions: Put bread and cheese in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour butter on this, then egg mixture. Refrigerate 1 or 2 days.
Before baking add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can milk, mixed. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°, uncovered.

title: picnic cookies
directions: Put cake mix into bowl.
Add beaten eggs, oil and water; blend well.
Roll in 1 to 2-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: simply delicious jello
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into saucepan; heat to boil. Dissolve jello in pineapple juice.
In large bowl, mix pineapple-jello mixture and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix Cool Whip into mixture with mixer on low speed.
(Cool Whip should be frozen.) Pour into bowl and chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and add to Bisquick and sausage.
Work in well. Form balls and place on well greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: onion spread
directions: Mix together; bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix shortening, brown sugar and egg. Stir in sour cream and blend in dry ingredients.
Drop teaspoon of cookie dough onto cookie sheet.
Cut dates in half and put a walnut half inside date.
Press open side of date onto center of each cookie and bake for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Coarsely mash avocados.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: indian corn stew
directions: Cook onions and green pepper with butter 5 minutes.
Add meat and brown well, stirring frequently.
Add corn, tomatoes, sugar and salt.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Stir in blended flour and water; cook for a few minutes and serve.

title: punch for 50
directions: Combine Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add pineapple juice and water. May store (refrigerate). When ready to serve, add ginger ale, ice and lemon juice.
Garnish with orange slices, lemon slices and frozen strawberry halves.

title: salmon chowder
directions: In a large pot, cover potatoes and onion with water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add salmon, milk and butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with saltines.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together, beating well.
Add flavoring.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, mixing well. Fold in cherries last.
Pour into a large greased tube pan.
Place in cold oven. Bake at 275° for 2 hours.
When still warm, top with frosting.

title: meringue pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until
foamy;
add
salt
and gradually add sugar and beat until
stiff.
Fold
in the vanilla, pecans and graham cracker crumbs.
Bake
in greased 9-inch pie pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: heavenly cake
directions: Cut top off cake, about 1/2-inch thick.
Using a spoon, remove inside of cake, leaving about 1/2-inch on sides for stability. Cut fruit into small pieces.
Mix with part of Cool Whip.
Spoon fruit mixture into cake until inside is full.
Place top back on and cover outside of cake with Cool Whip and garnish with fruit. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: anise-almond biscotti
directions: Position rack in center of oven and preheat to 350. Line baking sheet with parchment. Sift Flour, Baking Powder and Salt into medium bowl. Mix Sugar, melted Butter, 3 Eggs, Vanilla Extract and ground Aniseed in large bowl. Add flour mixture to egg mixture and stir with wooden spoon until well blended. Mix in Almonds.

title: pecan pie
directions: Dissolve sugar, syrup and butter in a saucepan over low heat. Pour over beaten eggs.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: steak soup
directions: In a large kettle, brown meat; drain and set aside.
Melt butter; add flour and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 3 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add consomme; cook until slightly thickened and until it comes to a boil.
Add vegetables, seasonings and meat.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: tavern sandwiches
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Add salt, pepper, butter, chili powder, catsup and dry mustard.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve on buns (like Sloppy Joes).
Serve 4 to 6 people.

title: hawaiian fajitas
directions: Cut a small pork roast into cubes and place in a skillet.
Add the green chiles; cover with lid and cook on low about 1 1/2 or 2 hours.
Do not remove lid.
Cook flour tortillas according to package directions.
Fill tortillas with pork mixture, tomatoes, green onions, Cheddar cheese and sour cream; fold up bottoms and roll.
Serve immediately.

title: easy chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips until smooth.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over sugar and mix well.
Spread into buttered shallow dish until thickness desired. Chill and cut into squares.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook vegeburger.
Combine all ingredients together, except Doritos and dressing.
Right before serving, add crushed Doritos and put dressing on last.
Mix all together.

title: cheese dream pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip topping mix as directed on package.
Beat cheese with sugar until creamy.
Blend in prepared whipped topping.
Serve as is or top with cup of pie filling.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: layered strawberry jello
directions: Have 1 cup sour cream held in reserve.
Mix first 6 ingredients and pour half of it in mold and chill.
Then spread with the sour cream.
Then pour the other half on top and chill. You can use an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex pan instead of mold.

title: crustless coconut custard pie
directions: Mix together milk, sugar, Bisquick and eggs.
Pour into a blender and blend for 2 minutes.
Add margarine, vanilla and coconut flavoring.
Blend for 2 more minutes.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch greased and floured pie dish.
Let stand 5 minutes; sprinkle with coconut, a cup or so.
Affix a foil collar, about 2 inches wide around pie dish, covering all but center of pie to prevent overbrowning.
Remove collar the last 10 minutes of baking if pie isn't a lovely golden brown.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until the center is set and golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: kelly's bean casserole
directions: Brown onion, hamburger and bacon.
Add remaining ingredients after draining grease off.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can be made ahead; if so, bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean and slice the
mushrooms.
Put in a bowl with the remaining ingredients.
Let stand at room temperature at least four hours before serving.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: Cover chicken with water; bring to boil and then simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove chicken; save liquid.
Remove chicken from the bone.
Saute celery and onion in butter until soft.
Add flour.
Cook, stirring until golden brown.
Add to broth along with chicken meat.
Salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Add noodles and cook until done.
Add half and half.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar, salt and vanilla in bowl and mix well. Pour into ice cream freezer, add condensed milk and stir well. Add milk to fill line on can and stir. Add crushed Butterfingers. (Easier to crush candy bars while still in wrappers.)

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Dip sliced tomatoes in buttermilk, then in dry mixture.
Fry in cooking oil until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: fall and winter salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cinnamon, 1 cup mandarin orange juice and enough water to make the one cup.
Add applesauce and nuts.
Refrigerate until set.
Decorate top with orange sections.

title: apricot chicken divine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine with oil in a baking pan.
Shake the chicken in a bag with the flour and salt.
Place in a single layer pan.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: corn to freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool, bag and freeze.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all items together, adding ketchup last.

title: baking a turkey
directions: Cook turkey parts like wings, giblets, neck parts, etc.
Take meat off the parts.
Save the juice for dressing and giblet gravy. Use the neck for giblet gravy, wings and other for dressing.
Cut up celery and onions.
Put in cornbread and biscuits.
Add poultry seasoning, salt, pepper and juice from turkey parts.
Mix all ingredients into a greased glass dish.
Make soupy.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, until done.

title: hobo dinners
directions: You also need 4 large squares of aluminum foil.

title: german pot roast
directions: Brown meat on all sides in Dutch oven.
When browning last small side, lower flame and add onion; saute.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Remove bone and cut or tear into small chunks.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together in bowl the chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Crush crackers and spread evenly over top.
Spoon melted margarine over cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown and bubbling.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in minimum amount of water; add parsley, butter, onion, salt and pepper.
Boil until tender.
Add milk, flour and eggs; then add to boiled potatoes.
Bring to a slow boil, stirring often.
Serve very hot.

title: hawaiian burgers
directions: Add chopped water chestnuts and soy sauce to ground beef. Cook burger to own taste (rare, medium, well done).
Place burger on top of grilled pineapple slice.
Top with cheese and pepper rings.

title: beef tomato eggplant casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and mashed garlic in oil.
Add flour and seasonings.
Stir and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove garlic.
Peel and slice eggplant.
Boil in salted water until just tender. Drain and set aside. Put browned meat on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange slices of cooked eggplant and sliced tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Toast the walnuts or pecan halves. Spread the nuts in a single layer in a shallow baking pan. Toast nuts in a 350° oven about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chuck roast "winner dinner"
directions: Turn on oven to 350°.
While preheating, place meat in center of a large piece of Reynolds wrap in a roasting pan.
Brush meat with A.1. sauce.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over it.
Spread with mushroom soup.
Wrap loosely in foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Vegetables, if so desired, may be added.

title: grandma's chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into chunks.
Brown in nonstick skillet.
Mix together chicken, mayonnaise and some juice off of the fruit.
Mix in fruit and nuts.
Refrigerate several hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sunday french bread
directions: Arrange bread in single layer in 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Beat eggs with milk, orange juice, sugar, vanilla and salt until well blended.
Pour over bread; turn slices to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: spicy turkey(working woman healthy)
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in margarine.
In large skillet, add turkey, other ingredients and 1/2 cup water.
Stir together and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 2 to 3.

title: l~b~j cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and spread in a greased and floured 9x13-inch dish.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Using large mixer bowl and low setting, beat eggs slightly; add sugar and blend well.
Add spices, pumpkin and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust.
Chill until set.
Top with pie filling. Refrigerate.

title: violet's banana cake
directions: Mash bananas and mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: dilly cucumbers
directions: In a bowl combine vinegar, oil, dill and sugar.
Add cucumbers and stir well.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and vegetable oil, margarine and egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to cream mixture alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in three 8-inch cake pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve jello in water; stir in sugar until dissolved.
Add juices.
Add ginger ale right before serving; chill ginger ale ahead.
Serves 50 to 75.

title: fruit chewies
directions: Spread nuts into bottom of greased and floured pan.
Mix margarine, brown sugar, eggs, flour and flavorings.
Pour batter over nuts.
Press candied fruit into top of batter.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.
Yields 36 bars.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine all 4 ingredients.
By hand, stir until well mixed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: cajun short ribs
directions: Place oil in skillet.
Coat short ribs with seasoning.
Heat oil until hot then add ribs and brown them well.
Add onion and pepper.
Lower heat and simmer about 30 to 45 minutes until onions and pepper are almost cooked to pieces.
Then add water.
Turn up heat and cook about 15 minutes.
Serve over white or wild rice.

title: german butter cookies(easy! delicious!)
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and oil and gradually add in dry ingredients.
Roll dough into small balls and flatten on cookie sheet with a glass which has been buttered or greased and dipped in sugar.
A crystal glass makes a pretty design; colored sugar also makes them pretty.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes, until slightly brown.
Yield: 4 to 6 dozen, depending on size.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add 2 cups cold water, marshmallows, pineapple and bananas.
Chill.
Combine egg, pineapple juice, sugar and flour.
Cook until thick.
Add cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Cool.
Whip Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add to cooled mixture.
Spread over jello. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: oven baked beef stew
directions: Slice potatoes; place half in large baking dish.
Brown meat, a few pieces at a time, with onion in oil in a large skillet.
Remove meat and onion as they brown to baking dish.
Top with remaining sliced potatoes.
Combine gravy, onion soup mix and water in a small bowl.
Pour over meat and potatoes; cover.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in frozen peas. Continue baking for 15 minutes longer or until meat is tender.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, salt and vanilla and beat thoroughly.
Add Milnot and milk; beat.
Makes 1 gallon (approximately).
Pour into electric or hand cranked ice cream freezer.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer 20 minutes.
Good on beef or poultry.

title: light and lively chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Place rice, vegetables and 1/2 can French fried onions around and under chicken.
Combine bouillon and Italian dressing; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes. Top with remaining onions.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
(I find it's better to place chicken on top of rice, then onions, vegetable bouillon and seasoning.)
Top with remaining onions.

title: leftover hot dog and hamburger buns
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on buns or bread as you would toast.
Brown on both sides.
Cut into strips when hard.

title: margie's rocky roads(oatmeal cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together the sugar, egg, butter, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bacon-tomato dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve cold with rye crackers.
