title: super dessert
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press in greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until slightly golden.
Beat cheese and sugar together.
Fold in 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix puddings with cold milk.
Spread on cheese layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on pudding layer.
Sprinkle chopped nuts or chocolate shavings on top.
Store overnight in refrigerator.

title: hot spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in big mouth quart jar.
Add 2 teaspoons mix and 1 cup boiling water in a cup for one serving, 8 heaping teaspoons to a quart.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and soup in ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle onion rings over top and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until onion rings are heated through.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well. In large pot, combine all ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours.
This recipe is a good camp dish, stretches easily.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: Cook and cool to lukewarm the oatmeal in the boiling water and butter.
In large mixing bowl, mix all remaining ingredients.
Add lukewarm oatmeal to ingredients in large mixing bowl, then add 5 cups to oatmeal and yeast mixture.
Knead; let rise to about twice its size.
Form into rolls or loaves.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 30 dinner rolls. Delicious hot or cold!

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Combine.
Grease pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes; longer if desired.
Do not cover.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil milk and sugar, then add browned sugar to boiling mixture.
Add butter and flavoring.
Boil until soft ball stage when tested in cold water.
Let cool, then beat until of spreading consistency.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two round 8-inch cake pans.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed or 300 hand strokes. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Add eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes, scraping occasionally.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 38 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Cool on cake racks completely.
Ice with chocolate frosting or a fluffy white icing.

title: chocolate candy cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add a slightly beaten egg yolk, flour and vanilla.
Mix well and spread 1/4-inch thick in a long, flat baking pan (preferably a jelly roll pan).
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place roast and vegetables in a large, covered roasting pan (no need to brown roast).
Mix seasoning and soups in a bowl. Pour over roast and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 300° for about 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours.
Makes great gravy.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: jazz pies
directions: Mix all together and place pie crust in muffin pans.
Fill 3/4 full with filling.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: sherried sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil the brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, orange peel and orange juice until it thickens.
Add raisins, butter, sherry and chopped nuts.

title: peanut brittle(about 2 pounds)
directions: Grease two 15 1/2 x 12-inch baking sheets.
Keep warm.
Place sugar, corn syrup and water in 3-quart casserole.
Cook on High 8 to 10 minutes or until soft ball stage is reached.*
Stir occasionally during cooking time.

title: kibbles and bits treats
directions: Put cereal in a large pan.
Melt the other 3 ingredients together.
Pour over cereal. Stir until well mixed.
Let set until cool. Shake a small amount of cereal at a time in a paper bag of powdered sugar.
Repeat until all are coated.
For fun, serve in a dog dish.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and margarine.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sausage breakfast dish
directions: Cook sausage to crumble.
Drain on paper towel.
Spread slices of bread with oleo.
Cut into cubes.
Place cubes in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sausage.
Top with cheese. Combine other ingredients and pour over sausage mixture.
Chill overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix all ingredients in large covered container. Refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: scampi
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and butter until tender. Transfer to a bowl.
Add shrimp, olive oil, parsley, garlic, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Toss together.
Arrange shrimp in large shallow baking pan.
Pour the sauce over the shrimp in the baking pan.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes.
Turn over and broil the other side. Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut-chocolate chip-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter with the sugars.
Add vanilla, milk and eggs. Beat in flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and coconut.
Bake about 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool on racks.

title: strawberry lemonade
directions: Combine lemon juice and strawerry puree.
Slowly add sugar to desired mix of tartness and sweetness.
Serve with ice.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and 3 cans milk.
Pour into heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Add remaining milk and set aside.
When cooled, add vanilla and peaches.
Pour into can and freeze.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in order listed.
Close to serving time, add fudge-strip cookies or chocolate frosted graham crackers, broken up.

title: marinade for beef
directions: Combine liquids and seasonings.
Pour over beef, cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Cook beef on grill, using the marinade as a basting sauce.

title: chicken spaghetti 1
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in melted margarine.
Add broth, soup, mushrooms and cooked chicken cubes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add cooked spaghetti to mixture.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash and pack okra in jars.
Add 1 teaspoon of dill seed and 1 clove garlic in each jar.
Mix vinegar and water and bring to a boil.
Pour over okra.
Seal quickly.
A pod or more of red hot pepper may be added, if desired.
This is ready to use in 6 weeks.

title: lo-cal frosty strawberry salad
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cheese.
Blend in strawberries and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze, then cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf and garnish with fresh whole strawberries.

title: chicken with brandied mushroom sauce
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil. Add chicken. Cook, turning once, until done. Transfer to serving platter.
Keep warm.
Add mushrooms to skillet. Saute 2 minutes. Stir in brandy and soy sauce. Cook 2 minutes longer. Spoon mushroom mixture over chicken.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Drain carrots and cool.
Mix with green peppers and onions. Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 12 hours or more. Will keep in refrigerator at least 2 weeks.

title: 10 minute spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute beef in skillet and drain.
Add all other ingredients. Heat to boiling; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: turkey crunch casserole
directions: Mix together turkey, eggs, mushrooms, celery and onion.
Stir soup into mayonnaise; toss with turkey mixture.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until mixture is bubbling.

title: spanish salad with apple-onion vinaigrette
directions: Remove stems from spinach, wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry. Set aside.
Combine sugar and next 4 ingredients, stirring with a wire whisk.
Gradually add oil, whisking rapidly until thoroughly blended.
Stir in chopped apple.
Stack several spinach leaves together; roll tightly.
Slice at 1/4 inch intervals, forming "ribbons."
Repeat with remaining leaves.
Arrange spinach on individual plates.
Drizzle with dressing.
Garnish, if desired.

title: date drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and water.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.

title: ripe olive and tomato cilantro salsa
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Add black pepper to taste. Serve salsa with corn chips.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion, salt and chili powder. Drain any extra grease. Add tomato sauce and simmer for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in small amount of water until done (about 20 minutes).
Drain.
Mix with margarine.
Add soup and grated cheese.
Add 1/2 cracker crumbs.
Mix all together.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over the top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and 1 unbeaten egg in bowl until crumbly.
Put sliced apples in a shallow, greased baking dish (6 x 10-inch).
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cover with mixture and pour 1/3 cup of butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: sweet vidalia onion scallops
directions: Peel and slice onions; melt 1/4 cup butter in skillet.
Add onions and green peppers together and cook until tender.
Stir in pimentos.
Place half of onion mix in shallow baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Repeat layers of onions and cheese.
Beat eggs with light cream, salt and pepper. Pour over onions.
Combine remaining cracker crumbs with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until set.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add applesauce with 1 teaspoon soda mixed in it.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and add evaporated milk, sugar, vanilla and salt. Pour into 5-quart ice cream freezer container and pour in the extra milk to the fill line of container.

title: choco-mint freeze
directions: Toss together wafer crumbs and the 4 tablespoons melted butter or margarine.
Reserve 1/4 cup of crumb mixture; press remaining mixture into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread with softened ice cream; freeze.
Melt the 1/2 cup butter and chocolate over low heat; gradually stir into egg yolks with confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Beat chocolate mixture until smooth; fold in egg whites. Spread chocolate mixture over ice cream; top with reserved crumb mixture; freeze.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry-lemon tea
directions: Press thawed strawberries through a sieve.
Mix with pineapple-orange drink, tea, lemon juice and sugar.
Serve over ice.
Makes 21 (4-ounce) servings.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Put in berries at once.
Stir until thawed.
Chill slightly.
Pour over creamed cheese mixture. Keep in refrigerator.
Great for dinner parties or potluck dinners.

title: prune pound cake
directions: Blend sugar, Wesson oil and eggs.
Blend well.
Sift flour and spices together.
Add to prune mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into floured and greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Start in cold oven.

title: low cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa and salt and mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool at least 1 hour before removing from pan.
This is a heavy, moist cake.

title: whole wheat potato rolls
directions: Mix shortening in hot potatoes.
Mix the rest as usual.
Use 1/3 whole wheat flour.
Let rise until double in size.
Roll out about 3/4-inch thick.
Cut like doughnuts, without the hole, or shape into balls.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until done.
Can also be made in sticky buns.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown the first 4 ingredients and drain. Add rest of ingredients. Mix all ingredients and simmer in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours.

title: peppers
directions: Wash and seed peppers. Cut into strips and pack in glass jars. Cover with equal amounts of water and vinegar. Pack in glass jars. They don't have to be sealed. You can pack whole peppers in a crock and cover with vinegar and water.
They will stay crisp all winter.

title: layered enchilada pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In frying pan, cook ground beef and onion until beef is brown.
Drain well.
Stri in seasoning, chilies, olives and tomato sauce.
In 2 1/2-quart round casserole dish, alternate layers of buttered tortillas, meat mixture and cheese, ending with cheese sprinkled on top.
Add water and cover with olives and chopped green onion.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream or guacamole.
This recipe can be prepared ahead of time.
You would add water just before cooking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: white dressing
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Gradually add milk and stir until smooth.
You may adjust sugar and vinegar to your taste.

title: three corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients and add to melted margarine.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine pancake mix, cornmeal, sugar, chili powder and cumin. Add water and beat well.
Dip franks in batter and drain excess batter over bowl.
In deep skillet, fry two at a time in hot fat (375°) for 1 to 2 minutes.
Insert a wooden skewer into one end of each frank.
Drain well on paper toweling.
Serve hot with mustard.

title: oven french fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into 6 spears.
In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, seasoned salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce. Add potatoes, coating each well. Spray a cookie sheet with nonstick coating.
Place all the potato spears on the cookie sheet, cut side up.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and potatoes are slightly blistered.

title: cinnamon apple waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs, milk, Wesson oil and apples; add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Use about 1/2 cup batter for each waffle.
Bake in hot waffle iron until golden brown.
Yield: 8 waffles.

title: party bean dip
directions: Brown ground turkey and dry onions in a large pan.
Add mashed beans, catsup, chili powder and hot sauce and heat.
Add chopped onion and cheese and heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla or nacho chips.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and chop finely.
Combine in a saucepan over low heat the following:
cheese and 1/4 cup butter.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion and seasonings.
Fold in the potatoes and turn into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.

title: southern tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in flours.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in oven preheated to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until beginning to brown.

title: fred's taco salad
directions: Wash and tear lettuce, making a bed on the bottom of the tray. Layer the tomatoes in.
Next, add the peppers and beans. Top them with the onion slices and cover them with the shredded cheese. Top with dressing.
For a finishing touch, just before serving add the crushed Doritos.

title: hot caramel apple cider
directions: Heat apple juice.
Blend cinnamon syrup and apple juice.
Top with whipped cream, and drizzle with caramel syrup.

title: ceylon spiced tea
directions: Combine.
Use one rounded teaspoonful for each cup of tea and brew for 5 to 6 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute the onion, peppers and garlic in olive oil.
Peel and dice eggplants.
Salt the eggplant and let it stand.
Peel and dice zucchini.
Wash and drain the eggplant.
Add to the sauteed mixture, then add zucchini, tomatoes, basil and sugar.
Season with salt to taste.
Stir and simmer.
Add parsley and bay leaf.

title: swans down white cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Add baking powder and salt.
Sift.
Cream shortening. Add sugar.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, fold (do not beat) into batter.
Makes two 8-inch pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Chop apples and set aside.
Beat oil, sugar and eggs on low speed until creamy.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder. Add flour to creamy mixture, a little at a time, making a stiff batter.
Mix apples and pecans; fold in by hand.
Grease a tube pan, but do not flour.
Pour in batter; bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-kidney bean casserole
directions: *One 16 ounce package frozen broccoli, thawed and drained, can be substituted for fresh broccoli.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.
Turn out and cook on wire rack.

title: hamburger rice hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger and onions.
Mix 2 cans of chicken rice soup, 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup, 1 1/2 cans of water.
Mix all together then 1 1/2 c. Uncle Ben's rice.
Bake 45 minutes - 1 hour at 375°.
Add Soy sauce on top (optional).
Feeds about 10 people.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Add 1 cup juice to pudding and add the fruit.
Can add bananas.

title: lemon chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except croutons.
Chill.
Just before serving, stir in croutons.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and let set overnight or at least 8 hours in refrigerator.
Serve with any vegetables.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion.
Drain fat.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and vinegar and stir well.
Add beans.
Put all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quail risotto
directions: Saute the onion in butter; add leek, green pepper and bacon. Cook until tender.
Stuff quail with mixture and place in a heavy, tightly covered pot and cook until tender.
Add rice, salt, pepper and tomato; stir.
Add stock to make approximately 2 2/3 cups liquid.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually then add baking powder and vanilla.
Next, fold in crackers and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Chill and spread with Cool Whip.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef with garlic and oil in saucepan; drain.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, parsley and seasonings; mix well. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Spread 1/4 of meat sauce in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer noodles, cheeses and remaining meat sauce 1/3 at a time in prepared dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Bake 5 minutes longer, uncovered.
Let stand several minutes; cut into squares and serve.

title: tangy cocktail sauce
directions: Combine ingredients; chill.
Serve with seafood.
Yield:
1/2 cup.
Carbohydrate 2 g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories per serving 8. Two tablespoons or less free food exchange.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: carrie's chicken casserole
directions: *If self-rising flour is used, omit baking powder.

title: maw maw's spaghetti and meatballs
directions: *We Italians call it gravy.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix well and bake in 8 x 13-inch greased pan for 40 minutes at 450° or until set.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(microwave)
directions: Place sugar, milk and melted butter in microwave. Cook 4 to 4 1/2 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: gumbo
directions: Mix in order. Cook chicken, onion and garlic until done.
Add chicken broth and Pace picante. Add peppers and sausage.
Thicken with cornstarch or flour
and put on cooked rice.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots and boil until fork-tender (in saltwater). Cool. Alternate layers of carrots, peppers and onion. Make marinade of soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard and sauce; mix well. Pour over layers and refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: farm style oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, buttermilk and vanilla in large bowl.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten cookies with bottom of glass dipped in water. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in a well-greased casserole dish.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Add sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil and cook for 2 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and quickly add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by tablespoons onto aluminum foil.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Using assorted metal cookie cutters, cut shapes out of bread. Spread with margarine or Miracle Whip.
Cut lunch meat and cheese out using same cookie cutters.
Garnish each sandwich with pickle slice or green olive.
For best results, be sure cookie cutters are sharp.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat eggs in large mixing bowl until lemon colored.
Add oranges.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt together.
Add to orange mixture.
Beat 4 minutes at low speed.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° (preheated oven) for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheesy carrot bake vegetable dish
directions: Mash cooked carrots with electric mixer.
Add margarine, beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in cracker meal, cheese, milk, minced onion, dill weed and seasoned salt.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart oven-safe ring mold. Bake in 350° oven 50 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 10 minutes.
Run knife around mold and remove.

title: quick and easy breadsticks
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Pour milk into flour. Stir to mix. Should be gooey, not stiff. Spoon onto a floured board. Lightly knead enough flour into dough until it can be patted into a rectangle about 8 to 9-inches by about 4-inches. Cut with a sharp knife (which you continue to run through the flour). Cut in half and again in halves until you have 12 breadsticks about 4-inches by 3/4-inch. Melt butter in an iron skillet. Roll sticks in butter and place in skillet. Bake about 10 to 15 minutes, until golden.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugars, pineapple and flavoring.
Take a large marshmallow and put sweet potato mixture around.
Roll in coconut.
Put balls in a greased dish and bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: grandma's magic bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs and mix together.
Sprinkle nuts over mixture, then sprinkle the chocolate bits, then the coconut in layers.
Spoon milk over the mixture to cover completely.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Cool 15 minutes.
Cut into strips.

title: katrina's appetizer
directions: Combine 2/3 caramels and both packages cream cheese in a mixer or food processor.
Mix until well blended, pour into decorative bowl.
Dribble remaining caramels on top and sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Serve with apples.
A little lemon juice on the apples will prevent browning.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Boil chicken and cool enough to chip chicken off bone.
Save chicken broth.
Mix cornmeal, grease and enough buttermilk to make a batter (like a cake).
Grease an iron frying pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: In
large
mixing bowl, blend margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mix until thoroughly combined. Stir in cereal and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls about 1 inch apart onto lightly
greased baking sheets.
Bake in 350° oven about 10
to 12	minutes
or
until
very
lightly browned.
Remove immediately from
pans.
Cool	on
wire rack or cloth.
Makes about 5	or 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.
Pecans can be substituted for walnuts.

title: gingersnaps
directions: In a large bowl beat brown sugar, molasses, Crisco and egg until fluffy.
In another bowl sift together remaining ingredients. Add dry ingredients gradually to sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Form dough into balls 1/2 inch in diameter.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Place balls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: killer rolls(overnight - easy)
directions: Grease Bundt pan with shortening.
Place 18 frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with pudding.
Mix brown sugar and butter.
Melt together until blended.
Pour over rolls and pudding.
Shake cinnamon over top and sprinkle pecans over top.
Cover pan with greased foil.
Place tea towel over foil.
Let rise overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then invert on plate.

title: crab cakes
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients and gently fold in crabmeat and bread crumbs. Shape into 10 patties. Heat 1/2 tablespoon butter and 1/2 tablespoon oil in large nonstick skillet on medium heat. Cook part of crab cakes 4 minutes on each side until brown. Drain on paper towel. Repeat with remaining butter and oil for rest of crab cakes.

title: weight watchers peanut butter pie
directions: Let Cool Whip soften slightly.	Add peanut butter to mix with mixer.
Pour into crust and freeze 3 hours.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix together and chill first 4 ingredients. Roll into balls. Melt chocolate and paraffin. Dip balls in chocolate mixture to cover thin.

title: mostaccioli
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground meat over medium heat until well done, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain excess fat; set meat aside.
Over medium heat in same skillet, cook onion in vegetable oil until golden, about 5 minutes.
Do not let onion turn brown.
Add garlic, pepper, tomato sauce, tomato paste, basil and oregano.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Nuts, raisins, chocolate chips, etc. may be added.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix well and beat for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325°
for 55 minutes.
When cake is done, let cool for 5 minutes.
Place on cake plate.
With sharp instrument make several holes in top of cake.
Pour glaze over top of cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Break chicken into pieces and put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix 1 1/2 cups broth with melted butter or margarine; add stuffing mix until well moistened.
Spread over chicken mixture and bake at 400° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: beef turnovers
directions: Combine crackers, flour and Parmesan.
Cut in butter or margarine.	Sprinkle cold water
over
mixture, one tablespoon at a time, mixing with fork.
Form into a ball.
Wrap in clear plastic.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Brown
ground
beef;
drain. Stir in spinach, mushrooms, spaghetti
sauce,
salt, basil and thyme; set aside.
On floured
surface,
roll
dough
1/8 inch thick.
Cut out 24 (4-inch) circles.
Place about 1 tablespoon of filling on half of each
circle.
Brush
edges
with beaten egg. Fold dough over filling to	form
a
half
circle.	Seal edges with fork.	Place on
greased
baking sheet.
Brush with more egg. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Cool and crumble.
Break broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Add cashews and toss ingredients together.
Combine the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together and pour over salad.
Let chill.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Toss cornflakes, coconut and nuts in large bowl. Combine sugar and syrup. Bring to a boil and boil a few minutes--not hard. Then add peanut butter. Pour over cornflakes; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or make balls by hand and place on wax paper.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Add green pepper and chopped onion to pan.
Cook until soft.
Add chunks of chicken and cook until chicken is done.
Add 1/4 cup of teriyaki sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Warm flour tortillas in microwave. Take out and add chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and roll into burrito.

title: chicken shells
directions: Boil chicken and prepare stuffing accordingly.
Mix cut-up chicken and stuffing together with sour cream.
Stuff cooked shells with chicken mixture and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 3/4 cup of water with 1 can cream of chicken soup and pour over stuffed shells.
Place Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: frisky sours
directions: In a blender container, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cover; blend just until mixed.
Serve over ice, if desired.
Makes 9 (4-ounce) servings.

title: 7-minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, salt, water and corn syrup in double boiler.
Beat one minute until thoroughly mixed.
Place over boiling water.
Beat at high speed for 7 minutes until stiff peaks form.
Pour into bowl.
Add almond extract and beat one minute until thick.
Fill and frost cake.
Sprinkle coconut over top and sides.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form in ball or logs.

title: chicken, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: In a large boiler, saute onion and celery in butter, then add soup.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and mix thoroughly.
Place in casserole dish.
Add broth if too dry.
Add grated cheese on top after casserole bubbles.
Can substitute shrimp for chicken.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine crumbs, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and fat or butter; mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts or raisins.
Turn into greased baking tin.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: scrumptious taties(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Boil potatoes; let sit until almost cool, then dice. Meanwhile, melt butter and mix with soup, cheese and onions. Blend with sour cream.
Add potatoes and toss.
Top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: swedish apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Pare and cut apples into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add dry ingredients, apples and nuts; mix well.
Bake in greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.
May be served hot or cold.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat egg in milk.
Add to dry mixture and stir with fork.
Spoon on top of whatever.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes, uncovered, then 5 to 7 minutes, covered.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Beat eggs and blend in meal.
Pour enough boiling water on to make mixture thick.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in very hot oil.
Fry until brown.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Grind cranberries in a food mill (meat grinder) with the orange and apple with peel.
Chop nuts.
Add nuts and sugar.
Makes 1 plus quart of cranberry sauce.

title: mushrooms in red wine
directions: Wash and slice the mushrooms.
Saute the onion in butter.
Put in mushrooms.
Cook until they are softened.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, seasoned salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add the red wine and continue cooking until the wine cooks down.
Serve warm. Great with steaks.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Beat all ingredients together with electric mixer.
Shape into a ball, then garnish with finely chopped pecans, parsley or cracked black pepper (personal preference).
Chill to set.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries and apples. Stir in sugar, nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch dish and freeze.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine beef, beans and spices.
Place four noodles in bottom of pan (13 x 9-inches).
Spread 1/2 mixture over noodles.
Top 4 more noodles and rest of meat mixture.
Top with rest of noodles. Combine water and salsa.
Pour over all.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and sugar well.
Pour melted butter over sugar and cracker mixture and mix well.
Pat this mixture in bottom of 8 x 11-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix in large mixing bowl, cream cheese (use 12 ounces if you like more cheese), eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix about 5 minutes (high speed) and pour mixture over crumb crust.
Place in a preheated 350° oven and bake for 20 minutes.
After 20 minutes, remove from oven and let cool thoroughly.
Take 1 can of blueberry pie filling and 1 tablespoon of fresh lemon juice and spread over cooled mixture.
Top with pint of whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Decorate as desired.
This can be made with fresh blueberries during season.
Strawberry Delight is good too!

title: mama's jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Pour in sugar, flour and vanilla. Pour on wax paper on greased pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Pull paper off.
Turn out on dish.
Put towel covered with powdered sugar.
Put jelly all over.
Roll up.
Slice.
It's ready to eat.

title: tuna fried rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Saute onion in oil over medium heat in 12-inch skillet or wok until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked rice and vegetables; cook and stir 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in pimento, soy sauce and tuna, being careful not to break up tuna.
Serve with additional soy sauce, if desired. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spiced tea(yields 20 servings)
directions: Combine.
Keep in covered jar.
Use 1 tablespoon to a cup of hot water.

title: puddin'!
directions: Use a heavy pot, either medium or large.
Put everything in, except the vanilla and fruit.
Cook on medium-high heat until thick, stirring constantly with a whisk.
Take off heat and stir in the rest.
Pour into a bowl and chill (2 hours or so).

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Brown hamburger and onions, drain fat off, add other ingredients and cook till done.
Serve warm.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt butter and chips in pan; add milk.
Then pour and mix into marshmallows and nuts.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Put in fridge overnight; cut into 1 x 1-inch squares.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Mix dressing ingredients and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: no-fat pineapple muffins
directions: Mix together.
Pour into sprayed muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins with 66 calories and 0 fat.

title: mamie eisenhower's frosted mint delight
directions: Have all ingredients chilled.
Melt the apple jelly and mix with crushed pineapple.
Mix the Jell-O with the jelly mixture. Dissolve the Jell-O in the pineapple juice.
Mix the Jell-O mixture with jelly mixture.
Whip the cream and fold into other mixture with a wooden spoon.
Place in freezer until solid, not frozen.
Serves 12 people.

title: chop soupy
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy pan; cover and place in a 300° oven for 3 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Or, after 3 hours, add carrots, potatoes and other vegetables.
Cook for another hour for a different stew.

title: cake icing
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients until thick.
Add the salt and vanilla.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Boil 4 quarts water and add half and half yellow and white corn meal.
Make thick batter and cover and cook 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: heath brunch coffee cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Reserve 1/2 of the mixture for later.
To half of the mixture, add the next 4 ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix together Heath bars, pecans and remainder of mixture.
Sprinkle over batter already in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lupes casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add mushroom soup and enchilada sauce. Mix well.
Layer meat, chips and cheese until all is gone and top with cheese.
Cook 20 minutes at 300°.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown hamburger, drain fat and add 30 ounces Ragu (set aside). Mix the following:
12 ounces Mozzarella, 16 ounces cottage cheese, parsley, Parmesan , 2 eggs, salt and pepper.
Boil noodles.
Drain and lay on wax paper to cool.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and cut carrots in fairly thick slices.
Boil until tender.
Put half of carrots in large bowl.
Cover with onion and pepper slices.
Add remaining carrots.
Do not stir.
Combine remaining ingredients for dressing, mixing well.
Pour over carrots.
Let stand overnight.
Stir before serving.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: zucchini pie snack
directions: Slice zucchini; add Bisquick.
Add all other ingredients. Grease cookie sheet and place mixture over the cooking sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into small squares.

title: eagle brand cake
directions: Bake cake following directions on package.
While warm, punch holes in top with straw.
Pour room temperature Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Smooth with spoon.
Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake; layer cherries and nuts.

title: green chile omelet
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the chopped green chiles in pan.
Spread 1 cup of shredded cheese on chiles.
Add eggs, milk and Bisquick in blender; pour over cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon in a bowl together.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add oil, eggs, and pumpkin and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9x13 inch baking pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hobo vegetables
directions: For each person place a carrot, potato and an onion on a large square of foil.
Add 1 tsp. unsalted margarine and pepper. Wrap tightly and seal. Place over hot coals for 45-60 minutes, turning occasionally until vegetables are done.
Yields four servings.

title: play doh
directions: Heat water, salt and food coloring; bring to a boil.
Mix flour, alum and Wesson oil in a bowl.
Mix together water and flour mixtures and knead until soft.

title: indian summer casserole
directions: Layer ingredients, starting and ending with creamed potatoes. Cook in preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with broken pieces of sliced cheese if preferred and cook for 5 minutes more.

title: nerds
directions: Melt bark and peanut butter in top of a double boiler.
Mix together with cereal and peanuts.
Spoon on a cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Set in freezer for 5 minutes, while preparing another tray.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, soda, salt, flour and spices together in large bowl.
Next, mix oil, eggs, water and pumpkin in medium bowl. Make a well in the dry ingredients and pour in liquid ingredients. Stir until moistened.
Bake at 350° in 3 loaf pans 7 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch for approximately 50 minutes.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Toss together potatoes, salt and celery.
Remove yolks from eggs.
Dice egg whites and add to potato mixture.
Blend cucumber, onion, mustard, salad dressing, vinegar and egg yolks in blender. Fold sour cream into mixture and then fold this dressing into potatoes.
Chill well.

title: four layer dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Crush vanilla wafers and add pecans.
Melt butter. Pour over mixture and mix.
Bake until crisp (20 minutes at 350°).
Make in spring-form pan.

title: yummy vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: cheese ball
directions: Remove cream cheese from refrigerator 1 hour before preparation.
Mix cream cheese, beef and onion thoroughly together.
Make into a ball.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve with crackers or rye bread.

title: spiced rice
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions, green pepper and raisins; saute until tender.
Stir in rice and spices.
Brown slightly.
Add broth; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover with tight fitting lid; simmer for 14 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Toss lightly and serve.

title: seared ahi tuna with green onion-wasabi sauce
directions: Whisk 1/2 cup water and wasabi powder in medium bowl to form smooth paste (or use tubed wasabi paste). Whisk in soy sauce, 2 tablespoon peanut oil, sherry, sesame oil and ginger. Stir in green onions. Set aside. Sprinkle tuna with salt and pepper. Grill on VERY hot grill. Sear quickly on both sides, about 3 minutes per side. Spoon cucumber onto center of plates. Top with tuna. Spoon sauce around. Garnish with radish sprouts. Serves 4.

title: oreo cake
directions: Butter a spring-form pan.
Pour kahlua in unwhipped cream in a large bowl and refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.
(Put beaters in refrigerator, too.)

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix.
Leave overnight and just before serving, add bananas.

title: all fools cake (chocolate)
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and sour milk; beat hard.
Sift cocoa, flour, salt and soda.
Add to first mixture and beat.
Add boiling water and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pumpkin loaves
directions: Lightly grease two 9 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder, soda and spices.
Set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer, beat sugar with butter just until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue beating until very light and fluffy. Beat in pumpkin at low speed.
Beat in flour and spice mixture. Add raisins and nuts.
Turn batter into prepared pans.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tested done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: old-fashioned dried apple stack cake(viola pace)
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and ginger.
In a separate bowl blend molasses, brown sugar, butter and eggs.
Stir dry ingredients into molasses mixture to form dough.
Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Divide dough into 6 equal parts. Roll out each piece of dough to fit a 9-inch cake pan.
Bake in well-greased and floured pans at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes six layers.
Cool layers before filling.

title: cottage cheese casserole
directions: Prepare noodles by package directions and set aside.

title: bacon-cheese quiche
directions: Sprinkle first 3 ingredients into pie crust.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: corn bread
directions: Melt bacon drippings in a 9-inch iron skillet until very hot. During this time, sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add buttermilk and egg; beat until batter is smooth.
Add 1/2 of drippings to batter and stir well.
Pour batter into skillet and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in casserole dish.
Bake until brown in a 350° oven, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: punkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Add liquids and pumpkin.
Mix well. Add raisins and nuts.
Fill three 1 pound coffee cans 2/3 full.
Grease and flour cans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with green pepper and onion.
Add both soups, water, mushrooms, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles according to package directions.

title: whole grain sally lunn
directions: Grease 10-inch pan or fluted tube pan.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large mixer bowl, combine milk, margarine, sugar and salt.
Stir in dissolved yeast, oats and eggs.
Add 1 cup flour; beat at medium speed on electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until double in volume, about 1 hour.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix the ground meats together with the raw rice.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery, onion tops and parsley.
Mix in soups. Season with red and black peppers.
Put in heavy casserole dish; cover with close fitting cover.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.

title: 7 up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients and chill until set.

title: mustard-herbed chicken breasts
directions: Flatten each chicken breast half by placing between two sheets of wax paper and pounding with a meat mallet to a thickness of about 1/4-inch.
Mix remaining ingredients in a small dish. Transfer to a large nonstick skillet and place over medium-high heat.
When hot, add chicken.
Cook, turning once, until meat is no longer pink in center, about 5 minutes total.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Line bottom of pie crust with berries and salt.
In a saucepan, put sugar and water and cornstarch and cook until thickened and add to pie boiling hot.
Let cool and add whipped cream.

title: diabetic strawberry bavarian
directions: Dissolve sugar-free jello in hot water.
Mix in cold water and pineapple juice.
Set aside to thicken slightly.
Whip the whipped topping.
Puree pineapple in a blender.
Mix pineapple with slightly thickened jello.
Fold in whipping cream.
Chill overnight.
Three-fourths cup equals 1 starch or 1 fruit.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese with sugar until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream, blending thoroughly.
Spoon into pie shell.
Spread cherries evenly over top.
Refrigerate pie overnight.

title: toad in a hole
directions: Cook sausages.
Heat oven to
Brush an 11 x 7-inch baking dish with sausage drippings.
Place sausages in single layer in baking dish.
Beat flour, milk, eggs and salt until smooth; pour over sausages.
Bake, uncovered, until puffed and golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: empire cheese soup
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients until soft.
Then add flour mixed with milk and cook until thickened.
After mixture is thickened, add cubed cheese and 1/4 cup cubed ham.

title: hot coffee dessert
directions: In a 2-cup glass measure, combine the coffee, milk and chocolate, mixing until well blended.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until very hot.
Turn into a large coffee mug and top with small mound of whipped cream.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients over moderate heat until mixture boils for a minute or less.
Add the beaten egg yolks, butter or margarine and lemon juice; mix well until thickened.
Pour into the baked pie shell.

title: paradise pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg whites stiff, gradually adding sugar.
Crumble crackers and fold with chopped nuts into beaten egg whites.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch pie pan 20 minutes.
Whip cream.
Top cooled pie with whipped cream and grated coconut.
Freeze until firm.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add ripe bananas and eggs.
Beat well. In a different bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Add to batter.
Add nuts.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together and pour over spinach in a Pyrex dish.
Bake for 1/2 hour or until brown and bubbly.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Cream potatoes with margarine and milk.
Do not add salt. Cool overnight.
Add onion salt, cream cheese, sour cream and 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese and mix well.
Top with remaining 1/2 package of Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grand marnier dipping sauce for fruit
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with half and half.
Using French whip, blend in Cool Whip and Grand Marnier.
Yields 5 pints.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: caramel popcorn pie
directions: Melt caramels in water in double boiler.
Mix with corn until well coated.
Slightly moisten hands.
Pack in rinsed 10-inch pie pan.
When top is dry, cut with knife dipped in cold water.
Also makes wonderful popcorn balls.
Wrap in waxed paper.

title: cake mix crinkles
directions: Mix well and form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in colored sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Combine in pie pan the chocolate wafer crumbs and butter; press on bottom and sides and freeze.

title: grandma's chess pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and cook in an unbaked pie shell at 350° until thick.
Allow to cool before slicing.

title: health candy
directions: Put the peanut butter, honey, nutmeg, powdered milk and wheat germ in a bowl.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into little balls.
Put the corn flakes into a plastic bag.
Crush the corn flakes in the bag with a rolling pin.
Roll the candy balls in the corn flakes. Now they're ready to eat.

title: my grandmother's canned tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut into quarters.
Cook on medium for 1 hour.
Add 1 teaspoon canning salt per quart of tomatoes while they are cooking.
Put in jars that are hot and sterilized; let seal.

title: beef and beans
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Stir in the next 5 ingredients. Heat until bubbly.
Pour into a 2-quart bake dish.
Place biscuits on top of meat; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pineapple smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth. Serves 4.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Cook; drain.
Put all chopped up ingredients in potatoes.
Add mayonnaise and stir.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: crispy ginger cookies
directions: Mix molasses, shortening, brown sugar and water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 4 hours or until firm. On floured board, roll out dough 1/2 at a time until paper thin. Cut with 2-inch round cookie cutter.
Place 1/2-inch apart on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes or until edges are barely brown.
Makes 48.

title: sara's angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Sit in refrigerator in a covered bowl for 24 hours.
It can be used anytime.
Take out the amount you want; knead it.
Cut out the biscuits you need.
Bake in a 450° preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop garlic, onion, mushroom stems, salami and cheese.
Melt margarine in a pan.
Saute chopped mixture of onion, garlic and stems, then add chopped salami and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.

title: fish bake
directions: Thinly slice potatoes and lightly brown in skillet.
Pan fry fish until brown.

title: fat free taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding corn chips just before serving.

title: neiman-marcus squares
directions: Beat 1 egg.
Mix with cake mix, one teaspoon vanilla and margarine.
Pat into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, remaining teaspoon vanilla and remaining 2 eggs and stir in confectioners sugar.
Add coconut and pecans.
Spread over cake. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Bake until golden brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Soak in water; do not re-use this water. Bring pork butt with water to boil with 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Cook until tender on simmer.
Add celery, beans and rice.
Cook until tender.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.

title: spiced waldorf salad
directions: Combine candies and 2 cups water in a saucepan.
Heat and stir until candy dissolves.
Add jello to mixture and dissolve.
Add 2 cups cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Add the remaining ingredients and refrigerate several hours until set.

title: impossible pie
directions: Clean heads.
Soak in salt water overnight.
Boil water and cook 7 minutes.
Drain.
Put in cold water 14 minutes.
Drain. Put in freezer bags.

title: corn country stuffed peppers(4 servings)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat. Saute the chicken in the fat, stirring to cook evenly.
Add onions, corn, paprika, salt and black pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Slice each pepper in half lengthwise. Seed and cut off stems.
Place pepper shells in an oiled baking dish.
Fill with the mixture.
Mix crumbs with the butter. Crumble over the tops.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until peppers are tender, yet firm.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown diced stems, tomatoes and onions in oil; remove from stove.
Add bread crumbs, cheese and parsley and stir.
Stuff the mushrooms and place on a greased baking sheet in a preheated oven at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 16.

title: tuna puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat egg yolks, mustard and pepper. Mix well.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Mix all ingredients.
Fold together and spoon into 2 cup casserole dish. Bake 20 minutes at 450°.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 luncheon servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo and pour over stuffing mix and seasoning.
Let set. Cook squash, drain and mash.
Add other vegetables, soup and sour cream.
Add half of cheese and half of stuffing mix to vegetable mixture.
Pour into greased casserole and top with remaining stuffing mix and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: supper in a pot
directions: In large pot, cook and drain ground beef, onion and garlic. Add spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Simmer 20 minutes. While this is simmering, cook macaroni shells.
Using a large casserole dish, layer 1/2 shells, 1/2 meat sauce and Provolone cheese.
Then 1/2 shells, 1/2 meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Cover and bake.
Remove cover last 5 minutes to let cheese melt. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: mary tyler moore's simple applesauce souffle and topping
directions: Spread the bread with butter or corn oil margarine using 1 teaspoon on each slice. Slice the bread in 1/4-inch cubes.
Put the bread cubes on a cookie sheet and put in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until bread cubes are toasted golden brown in color. Remove the bread from the oven and cool to room temperature.
Put half of the toasted bread cubes into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken. Cut into pieces, set aside. Combine onion, soups, salsa and milk; blend well. In 1 1/2 quart buttered casserole layer 1/2 the tortillas, chicken, sauce and cheese. Sprinkle with the green chilies. Repeat layers until all the ingredients are used, ending with cheese on top. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Blend
all
ingredients, except egg whites and paprika. Whip egg
whites until stiff and fold into other ingredients a little at	a time.
Turn into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake for 1 hour; uncover and bake 10 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick cheese fondue
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
In a 2 to 3-cup shallow baking dish, place the cheese. Bake until melted, 4 to 5 minutes.
Coarsely grind the pepper on top.
Set dish on a heatproof surface and serve with the apples or pears and walnut or other bread for guests to cut and use to scoop up fondue.
Serves 12.
Preparation time:
4 minutes. Cooking time:
5 minutes.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until cooked.
Cool; cut into bite size pieces. Mix all ingredients together, saving some cheese to sprinkle on top.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: creamy mushroom soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fresh mushrooms and wine in a large Dutch oven, and stir well.
Cook over heat until cheese is melted, stirring frequently.
Stir mushrooms into soup and cook over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir wine into soup just before serving.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add chicken, soup and green chilies.
Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop walnuts.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Stir to dissolve.
Chill until partially set, then add remaining ingredients.
Chill in oiled shallow pan for 4 or 5 hours (or in freezer for a shorter time).

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Bake crust at 425° for 3 minutes.

title: meatballs in sweet n sour sauce
directions: Mix hamburg, crackers, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Make meatballs.
Melt shortening and cook meatballs, then remove.
Keep warm.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth, then pour into skillet.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add meatballs, pineapple and peppers.
Heat through.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, coconut, cornflakes, vanilla and oatmeal in order given. Mix in separate bowl flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Add flour mixture and pecans (if desired) to shortening mixture. Mixture will be thick. Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees until done, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: new potatoes with basil cream sauce
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes. Drain carefully, leaving skins intact.
Keep potatoes warm. Combine wine and shallots in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Add whipping cream. Return to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes. Stir in basil, salt and pepper. Arrange potatoes on a serving plate.
Spoon sauce over potatoes. Serve immediately.
Yields 8 servings.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Sprinkle vegetables with salt and ice and soak for 3 hours in ice and cold water.
Drain and combine vinegar, sugar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil, cook cucumbers and onions in boiling syrup until cooked through.
Can in hot jars and seal at once.
Ready to eat in 24 hours.
Yields:
8 to 10 pints.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine milk, egg and sugar.
Beat with mixer.
Melt butter and pour 1/2 in baking dish and the other 1/2 in mixture.
Mix and pour in dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: nutty cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, sunflower kernels, peanuts, raisins and apples; toss gently.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir until smooth.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Toss gently to coat. Chill until serving time.
Yield:
3 1/2 cups.

title: creole sauce
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper until onion is clear.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Let simmer.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch and water.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn.
Melt margarine in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart dish.
Add light brown sugar, light corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil in microwave; boil for 2 minutes on High.
Remove; add soda and stir. Put popped corn into a large double strength grocery bag (do not salt or butter popcorn).
Pour hot syrup over popped corn.
Roll top of bag down and shake.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High; shake bag.
Microwave 30 seconds; shake again.
Microwave for another 30 seconds.
Put in pan; let cool.
Store in airtight container if there is any left after sampling.

title: chicken with rice and raisins
directions: Brown chicken on all sides in hot oil.
Remove chicken.
Add onion to drippings; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put chicken in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with tomato-rice mixture.
Cover and bake in hot oven (400°) for about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally and adding water if necessary. Makes 4 servings.

title: ranchero beef shortcake
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Add meat and cook, stirring until well browned.
Add remaining ingredients except
corn bread.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until meat is tender.

title: smith island pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until fluffy and light.
Add egg yolks one at a time, then salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour one cup at a time alternately with milk and water mixture. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured large tube pan.
Place in a cold oven; turn to 325°.
Bake 1 hour. Very moist and delicious!

title: cherry crisp
directions: Place the cherry pie filling
in
the
bottom
of a pie plate or baking dish.
Drizzle
lemon
juice
over
cherry pie filling. Melt butter and mix
with dry cake mix using a fork. Mixture will be crumbly.
Crumble over cherries.
Bake at 350° until top becomes light brown.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Bake chicken; cool.
Line 3 x 9 x 11-inch baking dish with tortillas, overlapping and breaking to fit.
Pour cup of broth over tortillas and let set while preparing topping.

title: spaghetti with artichoke and mushroom sauce
directions: Bring 4 to 6 quarts of salted water to a boil.
In a skillet, cook the garlic in olive oil over low heat until soft.
Add sliced mushrooms and cook until slightly softened.
Coarsely chop artichoke hearts and add with marinade from jar to skillet with parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook spaghetti in rapidly boiling water; drain.
Toss the sauce with hot cooked pasta.
Serves 4.

title: best rum cake ever made
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.,; check the rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure rum is of the highest quality, pour one level cup rum in a glass and drink it as fast as you can; repeat.
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy.
Add 1 seaspoon of thurgar and beat again.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey-bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill well.
Makes six 1/2 cup servings.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Mix crushed crackers and margarine.
Put in pie pan.
Put onions on top of crust.
Pour egg, milk and cheese over onions. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: french lemon pie
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, blend all other ingredients with eggs and mix well.
Add mixture to flour and sugar mixture and mix well again.
Pour into an unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake 30 minutes or until pie tests done.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix
everything except peaches. Drain peaches (save 1/2 cup juice) and chop.
Add to mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake
at
350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cherry-pineapple dessert
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour dry cake mix over the top of mixture.
Cut butter into 1/8 to 1/4-inch squares and place on top of cake mix (a 4 x 6-inch pattern usually works best).
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until top is golden brown.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Brown lightly onions and mushrooms in fat about 5 minutes. Remove.
Rub meat with flour.
Brown in fat on both sides.
Put roast in casserole and add remaining ingredients, mushrooms and onions.
Cover tightly and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or longer, if necessary.
Pour the remaining sauce in casserole over meat before serving.
In oven, cook at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef and put on paper towel to drain.
Add tomato, onion, lettuce and beans to ground beef.
Mix all these ingredients and refrigerate and when ready to serve add Catalina dressing and corn chips.

title: coolrise white bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast into 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir until dissolved. Add warm milk, sugar, salt, margarine and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth (about 1 minute).
Add 1 more cup of flour.
Beat vigorously at medium speed for 2 to 3 minutes.
Use enough of remaining flour to make a soft dough thick enough to put on floured board and knead.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes, until smooth and elastic.
Let rise double in size.
Form into 2 loaves.
Let rise double again.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: potato balls
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese and bread crumbs.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish and sprinkle with Parmesan and bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: cheese olives
directions: Blend
cheese with butter.
Mix in flour, salt, paprika and red
pepper
(sifted
together;
mix
well
into a dough. Refrigerate
for 1 hour.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of dough around each side
of
olive.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush package of Oreos in a food processor until fine grain; set aside.
Cream 1/2 cup margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix milk and pudding.
Combine cream cheese and pudding mixtures. Fold in Cool Whip.
Place lid of the Cool Whip upside-down in bottom of plant pot.
Starting with the Oreo crumbs, layer crumbs, pudding, crumbs, etc., ending with the crumbs.
Chill.
Just before serving, place flowers and shovel in pot.
This looks just like a potted plant.

title: the best chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients and mix with other ingredients.
Bake in a 300° to 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Parboil noodles in
salted
water;
drain.
Beat
eggs; add to noodles.
Add
sour
cream,
cottage
cheese and sugar. Pour into a 9 x
14-inch
Pyrex
pan	in which butter has been melted. Grate apples on top of mixture.
Add ground cinnamon. Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.	Cut into squares.
Serves 16 or more.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Shape ground beef into walnut sized balls. Saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Dip meat balls in rice.
Put in 2 1/2-quart casserole with rest of rice.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cover with sauce and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours uncovered.

title: south hill "fish pie"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut bass into chunks, set aside. Melt butter or margarine
in
microwave.
Crush	one sleeve of crackers in plastic bag,
pour
them
along with enough melted margarine to make bottom
crust	in
glass pie pan.
Press and add bass.
Mix second sleeve of crackers and remaining margarine and make crust as before.	Put on top.
Bake Fish Pie for 15 minutes.
The salt from crackers and margarine makes this a great tasting pie!
You will be surprised!

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Line a cookie sheet with wax paper.
Rinse strawberries; pat dry.
In a microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate morsels and shortening.
Stirring every 30 seconds, microwave on High until chocolate is melted, 1-2 minutes.
Dip half of each strawberry in melted chocolate.
Place on wax-paper lined cookie sheet. Refrigerate until chocolate is set.
Yield:
24 dipped strawberries.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Then add pineapple, soda, salt, baking powder and flour.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 18 minutes; watch closely.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and mace.
Add flour mixture to butter and sugar.
Mix alternately with bananas.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Bread will have a big crack in center.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Arrange tomatoes in dish.
Combine oil, vinegar and next 4 seasonings; spoon over tomatoes.
Cover.
Chill 2 to 3 hours, basting occasionally.

title: grilled cabbage
directions: Wash cabbage and totally core.
Fill cored center with sugar and butter.
Pack butter into cored center.
Spread any remaining butter on outside of cabbage.
Wrap prepared cabbage in foil. Cook on preheated outside grill for 2 hours or until tender.

title: apricot salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O in usual manner.
Let cool and add pineapple, bananas
and marshmallows.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.

title: apple sauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add more Flour if needed.

title: shrimp mariniere
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter and set aside.
In large heavy skillet or Dutch oven, melt remaining butter and saute onions until tender.
Blend in flour and cook slowly for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Add salt, pepper and wine.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer and stir 10 minutes to thicken sauce.
Add shrimp and mushrooms, stirring lightly for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and quickly beat in egg yolks.
Spoon into 6 large ramekins or 12 small ramekins (as appetizers).
Sprinkle with paprika and heat under broiler.
This can also be served from a chafing dish over toast points.
Freezes well.

title: quick white icing
directions: Mix together salt, sugar, syrup and water.
Stir over heat until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a slight boil.
Beat egg white until fluffy.
Gradually pour hot syrup over beaten egg white.
Continue beating egg white.
Add vanilla.
Beat until icing stands in peaks.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Sift and measure flour; blend all dry ingredients together, then stir in shortening mixture.
Make 1-inch little balls of dough. Roll balls in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Put 1 whole tomato or half, depending on number of chops, on each chop.
Pour juice of tomatoes over chops.
May need to add more tomato juice.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon salt over everything.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken delight
directions: Put 2 tablespoons shortening in skillet.
Split chicken breast into 4 pieces; remove skins.
Lightly flour and brown breasts. Remove breasts; pour off shortening.
In skillet mix chicken mushroom soup, water, milk and thyme.
Stir well.
Add mixed veggies (drained) and parsley.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 2.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with hands.
Make into walnut size balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 12 minutes.

title: quiche florentine
directions: Combine chicken, soup, grated cheese, eggs (beaten), cottage cheese, water chestnuts (drained), spinach (drained) and onion. This may be frozen in 2 small freezer bags. Thaw and pour each into a frozen pie shell. Cover with Cheddar cheese slices (optional). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: english-style scones(diabetic)
directions: Beat 2 eggs with cream and vanilla; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in dates and raisins.
Add egg mixture.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Flour hands; knead dough 4 times on floured surface.
Place dough on greased cookie sheet.
Pat into 8-inch circle.
Using sharp knife, score dough into 6 wedges, cutting 3/4 way into dough.
Beat remaining egg; add water to egg.
Brush onto dough.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into wedges and serve with jelly or whipped cream.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil with electric mixer.
Add eggs, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture, beating well. Fold in carrots, raisins and nuts.
Pour batter in greased layer pans.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: thelma's chocolate pie
directions: Mix
flour,
sugar
and cocoa;	add milk and egg yolks. Boil until thick, constantly stirring.
Remove from heat; add butter (or margarine) and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into cooked pie shell. Beat
egg	whites,
pour
on top and broil in oven until brown.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Layer refried beans in bottom of a 9 x 9 baking pan.
Mix ground beef, onion soup and mild taco sauce.
Spread mixture on top of the refried beans.
Spread sour cream on top of this mixture. Sprinkle the top with cheddar cheese and black olives.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Mix the soup, milk, black pepper and butter.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, arrange onion slices.
Put roughly crushed potato chips on top.
Pour soup mixture over chips and then cover with grated Cheddar or Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: artichoke frittata
directions: Drain marinade into a frying pan (from 1 jar).
Drain other jar and use elsewhere.
Chop all artichokes, set aside.
Heat marinade in frying pan over medium heat; add onion and garlic and cook, stirring until onion is limp.

title: picante sauce
directions: Blanch tomatoes for 1 minute in boiling water.	Dip in cold water; peel, core and cut up. Quarter onions. Slice up peppers. Put in blender and blend until smooth.

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine onion, rice and hot broth. Bring to boil.
Place in glass baking dish and cover.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve and listen for compliments.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Rinse and peel shrimp; refrigerate.
Use shells for stock.

title: whipped potatoes paprika
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling, salted water until tender, then drain.
Add the cream cheese, butter, salt, pepper and enough milk for desired consistency.
Beat with an electric mixer until smooth and fluffy.
Place in a serving dish and sprinkle with paprika. Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk and pepper; mix well.
Stir in beans and 2/3's French onions.
Bake at 350° or until hot.
Stir; sprinkle 2/3 cup onions.
Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden.

title: paksiw na isda(boiled pickled fish)
directions: Cut fish into 5 slices.
Place in a stainless pan.
Add all other ingredients; cover and bring to a boil.
Let simmer about 10 minutes, turning fish once to cook evenly.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Split and remove skin from chicken breasts.
Arrange in a baking dish.
Place 1 slice of cheese on each piece.
Mix together chicken soup with dry white wine.
Spoon evenly over chicken.

title: chili
directions: Crumble ground beef in 2-quart microwavable casserole.
Stir in onion.
Cover with glass lid and microwave on High for 5 minutes. Drain and stir in remaining ingredients.
Recover and microwave on Roast for 12 to 14 minutes or until hot.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable fettucini
directions: Grease a skillet with Pam.
Brown whatever fresh vegetables you want, i.e., 1 onion, 1 carrot, 1 green pepper.
Shake oregano, pepper and sometimes a little seasoned salt on this.
Brown a few minutes; when browned, turn off and add light margarine.
In another dish with a lid, shake milk, cornstarch and pepper.
Pour this over the vegetables in the skillet.
Add chicken bouillon or granules, then add cauliflower and mushrooms.
Shake Parmesan cheese over this and add more oregano.
Let simmer, covered, for a few minutes, checking to see that it is not too thick; if it is, add a little milk.
If it is too thin, add a little more cornstarch. Let it cook a couple minutes, covered.
Add fresh broccoli for only 2 minutes or so (should be crispy).
Cook and drain any type of noodles.
Shake Parmesan cheese on them after they are drained.

title: ranch dressing
directions: Mix well and put on salad.

title: cheese and sausage strata
directions: Mix sausage, mushrooms, onions, cheese and bread cubes and put in an 8-inch square pan, slightly oiled.
Beat together the milk, eggs and mustard; pour over sausage mix.
Refrigerate several hours.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown. Let sit 10 minutes and serve.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Arrange 1 can green chilies in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover with 1/2 of grated sharp Cheddar.
Layer last can of chilies over cheese.
Layer the last half of Cheddar cheese over this. Mix the evaporated milk, eggs, cornmeal, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over chilies and cheese.
Sprinkle half of shredded Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Over this pour the tomato sauce and top with the last half of the Monterey Jack. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in a large frypan.
Cover with cheese slices. Evenly distribute tomatoes over cheese.
Cover casserole with noodles, add water and juice from tomatoes so that pan is about 1/2 full.
Cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until noodles are done.
Check occasionally to see that some liquid remains in pan for cooking.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine first five ingredients; mix and let stand overnight. Rinse and drain twice.
Then combine rest of ingredients with mix and bring to a boil for 20 minutes.
Place in clean (hot) jars and seal.
Process for 5 minutes.

title: dot edge's spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions together until meat is very brown.
Drain fat.
Add tomato paste and hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Serve over hot noodles and top with grated cheese.
If sauce is too thick, add a little water to desired consistency.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Combine all thoroughly and put into 2 loaf pans. Sprinkle tops with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: mexican cornbread salad
directions: Follow directions and bake the Mexican cornbread. Mix all the ingredients in with the crumbled cornbread. Refrigerate before serving.

title: mounds
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients.
Let set 2 hours.
Melt the wax and chocolate block or chips.
Roll balls; dip in wax and chocolate.
Lay out on wax paper.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion in large frying pan.
Blend in tomatoes, enchilada sauce, olives with liquid from can, salt, garlic and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes (at least, otherwise sauce will be too thin).
Stir occasionally.

title: green bean and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute butter, onions and mushrooms.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, thyme and marjoram.
Gradually add milk.
Stir constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese.
Stir in beans.
Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes.
Can be made a day ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix it with the Cool Whip.
Add other ingredients; mix well and freeze.
Keep frozen.
Take out a little before mealtime so that it will thaw enough to cut easily.
This is great for the holidays!

title: frozen crunchy punch(by:  amy allen)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar, hot water, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Freeze in milk carton; set out 3 hours before serving.
Cut out of milk carton and pour 7-Up over the top and serve.

title: quick borscht
directions: Heat together beef broth, beets (with juice), cabbage, onion and sugar to boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer gently 5 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and chill thoroughly.
Top each serving with a spoonful of sour cream.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Thaw bread in refrigerator overnight.
Roll dough into 24 (1 1/2-inch) balls (12 balls from each loaf of bread).
Roll each ball into roll (14-inches long).
Place pretzels 1 inch apart on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Combine egg white and water.
Brush on pretzels.
Try making the letters of the alphabet or your name with pretzel dough.
Sprinkle with salt if you desire.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 pretzels.

title: one hundred year old pound cake
