directions: Beat egg yolks and whites separately.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, then flour in which baking powder has been added. Flavor to taste (vanilla or lemon).

title: grandma craig's french onion soup
directions: In a 4-quart pan, saute onions in butter and oil for 15 minutes.
Add sugar and salt.
Continue cooking for 30 minutes, stirring with wooden spoon.

title: grilled cornish hens(serving size: 2)
directions: Brush meat side of each hen liberally with the teriyaki sauce 30 minutes before grilling.
Grill on low to medium coals, turning every 5 to 10 minutes and basting each time.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour, until meat is tender and juices run clear.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil berries until they pop.
Stir in marshmallows; allow to melt.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until it sets.

title: cheese stuffed peppers(kentucky style)
directions: Slice the top off each pepper.
Wash and core the peppers. Parboil for 5 minutes.

title: orange glazed chicken breasts
directions: Spray medium nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Heat over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken; cook 4 minutes. Turn chicken; cook an additional 4 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet; keep warm.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice and cook potatoes (until mostly done).
Saute your onions, celery and pepper.
Fry your bacon; drain and crumble (or substitute for Bacon Bits).
(Your onions can also be substitute for green onions.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
In separate bowl, add flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and nuts.
Mix lightly.
Add to egg mixture and blend.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini to mixture.
Divide into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick is clean.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries and pineapple.
Congeal.
Make topping of cream cheese, sour cream, nuts, sugar and vanilla.
Mix and spread on top of congealed Jell-O.
Refrigerate until served.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix and bring to a rolling boil. Cook for 2 additional minutes. Stir constantly as icing may stick to boiler.
Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Nuts may be added also.

title: holiday cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: pot pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine Bisquick and milk. Drop on top to form biscuits.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Make into long roll and refrigerate (wrapped) overnight.
Next day, slice into 1/4-inch slices and bake on greased cookie sheets at 400° for about 5 minutes or until golden.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all of ingredients.
Top with crackers and butter.
Put in oven and bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: cherry dumplings
directions: Cream 1/2 cup sugar and oleo.
Add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla, milk, then flour and baking powder.

title: saffron rice bake
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
When rice is done, stir in oleo, soup and Mexicorn.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Jell-O in 6 cups boiling water.
Add juice and flavorings; mix.
Pour into 1 gallon container and fill almost to top with water and freeze or use at once, if desired.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add other ingredients to macaroni and marinate overnight in dressing.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: *May substitute 1/2 cup chicken broth.

title: south seas cream cake
directions: Place 1 cup crumbs in ungreased 8-inch square pan. Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Spread over crumbs. Combine cream, nuts and pineapple. Spread over mixture, then sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Refrigerate for 12 hours. Cut into squares.
Makes 8 servings.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together in a double boiler; set aside.

title: quick beef with broccoli
directions: Slice steak diagonally across grain into thin strips.
Coat wok with oil and stir-fry steaks until done.
Remove steak and set aside.
Coat wok and stir-fry broccoli 3 minutes.
Add tomato, onion and garlic.
Cook until broccoli is done.
In small bowl, mix cornstarch, wine and soy sauce.
Remove vegetable mixture from wok and put cornstarch mixture into wok; cook until it becomes thick, then add everything back into the wok.
Mix well and serve over rice.

title: broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: jamaican peas and rice
directions: Wash peas.
Boil in 4 cups water for 2 minutes.
Turn off heat. Cover and let sit one hour.
After 1 hour, boil covered until tender.

title: best ever cake
directions: Stir with wooden spoon (do not beat).
Grease and flour pan. Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes.
Check closely. Cool cake and frost or powder sugar top.

title: cheddar nut bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Combine baking mix, cheese, evaporated milk, water, nuts and egg.
Mix vigorously 30 seconds or until blended.
Spoon into buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: polish pot roast
directions: Soak dry mushrooms in water about 3 hours.
Drain.
In large pot, brown roast.
Add all above ingredients.
Cook on stove top 2 to 3 hours until tender.
During last 1/2 hour of cooking, add sour cream.
Mix to make a sauce.

title: taco dish
directions: Brown and drain the ground beef.
Add the chili powder, salt and pepper and can of diced tomatoes; heat through.
Cover the bottom of a cake pan with tortillas.
Pour the beef mixture over the tortillas and add another layer of tortillas over that.
Set aside.

title: sweet grahams
directions: Bring sugar, butter and oleo to boil.
Stir frequently.
Boil 5 to 8 minutes gently.
Pour over grahams.
Sprinkle nuts over all.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: refreshing lemon-lime drink
directions: In a large container, combine the lime and lemonade concentrate and orange extract. Stir in water. Just before serving, stir in lemon-lime soda. Serve over ice. Garnish with lemon and lime slices.
Yield: 3 quarts.

title: swiss steak
directions: Rub salt and pepper into steak.
Dredge with flour.
Brown quickly on both sides in hot fat with onion.
Add tomatoes; cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: chili
directions: In large skillet, cook ground chuck, onion and garlic until meat is brown and onion and garlic are tender.
Drain off fat. Return to heat.
Add tomatoes and seasoning.
Mix well.
When bubbly, reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Beans may be added, if desired (two 15 ounce cans pinto beans).
If beans are added, simmer 15 minutes longer.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water until all the water is cooked dry.
Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and soda together.
Add eggs, oil and applesauce.
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes until well mixed, then add fruit cocktail and raisins and 1 cup nuts, if desired.
Bake in tube pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and water; cool.
Add the juices and the bananas and freeze.

title: cool carrots
directions: Heat oil, vinegar and sugar.
Let carrots cool.
Mix in soup with the heated oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over the carrots and add the bell pepper and onion.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: diabetic applesauce cookies
directions: Get dough and get chocolate chips.
Make little balls.
Put them in the oven for 30 minutes if you think that's long enough.

title: black bean dip
directions: Mash beans.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make bread crumbs out of the bread. Dice onion and green pepper.
Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to suit yourself.
Put it in a meat loaf pan and cover with additional catsup.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: squash mix with ham
directions: Wash, trim and slice the squash.
Saute onions and celery in the heated butter until onions are transparent.
Stir in squash, ham, chervil, salt, red pepper flakes and water.
Cover and simmer about 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, shaking pan frequently.
Transfer to serving dish.
Sprinkle with additional red pepper flakes, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dice apples, celery and nuts.
Combine these with the fruit and gently toss together.
Make dressing by combining the topping and yogurt and add to the salad.
Mix well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients until smooth.
Add milk and Cool Whip.
Beat 1 minute longer or until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Serve chilled.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut potatoes into lengthwise halves and scoop out pulp from potatoes into a medium bowl, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Mash pulp; reserve shells.

title: cheeseburger logs
directions: Combine ground beef, cereal, bread crumbs, ketchup, salt, pepper and egg.
Mix well.
Form into 8 logs to fit buns.
Make groove down center of each log.
Cut cheese into narrow strips. Press into groove.
Broil 3 to 5-inches from heat, 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Serve in buns.
Serves 8.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: Microwave Directions:
In a 4-quart microwave-safe bowl, cook bacon at full power until crisp, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add potatoes, onion and garlic; stir to coat with bacon drippings. Cover bowl with plastic wrap; microwave at full power 5 minutes. Add broth and red pepper; cover.
Return to microwave and cook until potatoes are tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
In separate bowl, stir 2 tablespoons milk into cornstarch.
Add to potatoes with remaining milk, salt, corn and green peppers.
Stir well. Cover and cook, stirring twice, until vegetables are just tender, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in green onion and parsley.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: triple chocolate fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil or waxed paper.
Melt chocolate in a saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until creamy.
Add vanilla and salt.
Gradually add sugar and beat until smooth.
Beat melted chocolate into cream cheese mixture, add nuts and mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Refrigerate until firm (about 1 hour).
Cut into squares.

title: milk frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add sugar and milk.
Stir; heat to boiling.
Boil about 10 more minutes.
Take from heat; beat until thick enough to spread, then add flavoring.
Pour over cake.

title: party chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Remove meat from bones and cube. Mix the oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt.
Marinate chicken. Refrigerate.
Add the orange sections, pineapple, grapes, almonds and celery. Cook rice until tender in boiling salted water.
Drain and blanch.
Add to salad. Toss with 1 quart of mayonnaise. Refrigerate.
Makes 25 servings.

title: chicken doritos casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender, then debone it.
Crumble Doritos in a 9 x 12-inch ovenproof dish.
Lay chopped chicken on top of chips. Bring soup, broth, tomatoes, onion and pepper to a boil, then pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Grate Cheddar cheese over top and bake until cheese melts.
Serve hot!

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and wash sweet potatoes.
Add water, potatoes, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Cook for 30 minutes slow, then add cornstarch and cook 5 minutes.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Pare and core eggplant and cook in water 5 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well and shape into 8 patties.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown on each side.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 10 1/2-inch skillet or 2-quart baking dish.
Set aside.
Brown sausage and onion in medium skillet; drain well. Combine eggs, cornmeal, corn, milk and oil. Pour half of the cornmeal mixture into prepared dish; sprinkle with sausage mixture and cheese.
Pour remaining batter over top. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring undrained pineapple and sugar to a boil. Add jello, then cream cheese. Stir until dissolved. Remove from heat. Add ice water, then celery and nuts. Put in 9 x 13 dish and refrigerate. When it starts to congeal, stir in Cool Whip. When set, cut in squares to serve.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately one hour.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Flour fruit and nuts with 1 cup flour. Add vanilla; fold in flour.
Add nuts and fruit.
Bake in slow oven (250°) for 2 1/2 hours or tested done.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Skin, debone, and chop fine the cooked chicken.
Combine all ingredients, except tortillas.
Spread mixture on tortillas.
Roll up tortillas, refrigerate covered 5 hours or overnight.
Slice 1/4 inch thick to serve.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Add spinach to the rest of ingredients and mix together in a large bowl.
Turn mixture into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until set.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and salt. Add pecans and vanilla. Gradually blend in flour and mix thoroughly. Roll into balls or crescents.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: aunt ruby's peach delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in 9 x 12-inch or larger baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar well and spread over crust.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
Place peaches on second layer.
Mix sugar, jello and flour together; stir in water.
Cook over medium heat until clear.
Cool.
Pour over peaches.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese (microwave 30 to 40 seconds) on bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Scramble cook hamburg in frypan; drain fat.
Add salsa to hamburg and mix.
Spread mixture on cream cheese.
Spread Cheddar cheese and Monterey Jack on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: swish meat balls
directions: Mix together above ingredients; cover and refrigerate 2 hours. Make balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Drain on paper towels.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken. Rinse and pat chicken breasts dry. Separate skin from flesh, leaving skin attached at center of each breast. Place a fourth of stuffing under the skin of each breast. Tuck skin edges under; secure with toothpicks if necessary. Place breasts in a baking pan skin side up and dot with butter. Bake at 350° about 35 to 45 minutes, basting every 10 minutes with juices.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain fruit thoroughly before adding.
Mix everything together.
Chill and serve.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well.
Beat in molasses, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually blend in dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Chill dough for 2 hours.
Roll to 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness on a lightly floured pastry canvas.
Cut cookies with floured cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: extra-easy microwave lasagne
directions: Puree tomatoes with tomato paste in blender until smooth. Stir in parsley, oregano and basil; set aside.
In a 2-quart baking dish, break up sausage with spoon.
Stir in onion and garlic.
Cover with wax paper and microwave 4 minutes on High setting.
Stir and microwave 4 more minutes or until sausage loses its pink color.
Pour off fat and stir in half of the spaghetti sauce mix.
Spoon cottage cheese evenly over sausage mixture. Arrange noodles on top.
Sprinkle with remaining spaghetti sauce mix.
Pour tomato mixture over noodles.
Press down gently with spoon to be sure all the noodles are moistened.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn. Microwave 10 more minutes or until noodles are tender.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Microwave, uncovered, for 2 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Microwave:
Place beans in medium bowl.
Cover and cook on High 9 minutes, stirring twice. Drain.
In a 1 1/2-quart bowl, stir soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper until smooth.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can onions. Cover and heat on High 7 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring once during cooking.
Sprinkle with remaining onions.
Cook, uncovered, 1 minute.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken, beef and pork until it tears all to pieces. Take it out of the stock and let it cool.
Take the stock and put it on the stove and let it cook real slow.
Take the tomatoes and mash it up real good and put it in the stock.
Grind your onions and celery.
Put it in the stock; keep it low and let it cook slowly.
Grind your chicken, pork and beef.
Put it in the stock.
Stir real good.
Grind corn and put it in and let it cook slowly for 1 hour or longer.
If it is too thick, add water.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: "Grant me the bread of Thy wisdom, Lord; let it be the staff that sustains my life.
Teach me to walk always in your righteous ways, to be your servant, that I may be free.
Send out your light and truth in the land, so that all men may know and love Thee."

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise and spread over top, being sure to seal edges.
Sprinkle sugar over this mixture and top with the shredded cheese and bacon bits. This will keep in the refrigerator for a week.

title: corn and sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage, onions, pepper and mushrooms. Drain. In large bowl, mix all ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes or until golden brown and a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Serves 12 to 15.

title: crab meat muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on English muffins.
Cut into quarters.
Broil until golden brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish with crescent rolls.
Pat together at seams.
Cook sausage and drain; crumble over rolls.
Combine eggs, sour cream, salt and cheese.
Pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes (will continue cooking after removed, so don't overcook).

title: peanut butter cookies(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter; add sweetener and baking powder.
Add egg yolks and milk; mix well.
Divide into eight 1-inch cookies and press with fork to flatten.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cranberry sauce and mix well.
Let cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Mix celery, onion and cream cheese. Season with salt and pepper or seasoned salt.
Divide rolls into squares.
Spoon 1 tablespoon chicken mixture in center and close (pinching on the seams).
Place on a cookie sheet. Cook 1 minute longer than directions on crescent package or until golden brown.
Use temperature on Pillsbury can.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese; beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Freeze until firm.

title: old-fashioned southern fried chicken
directions: In small
bowl,
mix
syrup and water.
Separately, mix flour, salt,
pepper and oregano.
First, dip chicken in syrup mixture, then
in
flour
mixture.
In
deep
skillet, pour in large amount
of oil.
(Oil should cover chicken 1/2 way up.) Fry
until brown;
turn
and brown other side (2 to 4 minutes each side). Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburg.
Drain off fat.
Add taco sauce, corn and cooked macaroni; cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Put in greased casserole. Cover with grated cheese and top with crushed Doritos.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage with salt until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain. Mix soup, milk and cheese and pour over cabbage in casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: easy asparagus casserole
directions: Cut asparagus into 1-inch pieces.
Make a layer of asparagus, layer of sliced eggs and a layer of soup, then repeat.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs (melt butter and crumble cracker crumbs in it).
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in large iron skillet.
Stir in sugar and arrange pineapple slices on sugar. Decorate by placing cherries in the middle of pineapple.

title: yellow cake deluxe
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, creaming until light.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Beat 1 minute.
Bake in 2 greased and lightly floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pans in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool.
Fill with Lemon Filling. Frost with Seven Minute Frosting.

title: sugarless apple bundt cake
directions: Combine diced apples, apple juice, water and raisins in a bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and store in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours. Sift both flours, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice into a large bowl.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; fold into flour mixture.
Add apple-raisin mixture, including juice.
Add vanilla and cereal.
Stir well.
Pour into a Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn out onto a large sheet of aluminum foil.
Wrap completely in foil for several hours before serving.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine the Kool-Aid, sugar, orange juice and lemonade.
Mix well, then add water, Vernors and club soda.
Mix well.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Simmer ingredients for 10 minutes.
Pour over fish.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours before cooking.

title: english raisin scones
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and soda into bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk and raisins and stir until well blended.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
On a floured surface, roll each part into circle about 1/3-inch thick.
Cut each circle into 5 wedges.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush top with egg white.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 15 scones.

title: margie's under the sink pickles
directions: Bring to boil the 2-quarts water, salt and vinegar.
Cool to warm.
Pack sliced, fresh cucumbers, onion, clove of garlic and dill in a gallon jug.
Pour the warm liquid over.
Put on lid (loose), then put in cabinet under the sink for 2 days and nights. Next, put in refrigerator.
Ready to eat in 5 days.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together; add peanut butter, eggs, vanilla and corn syrup.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant 1/2 inch thick.
Mix fine bread crumbs and grated Parmesan cheese in equal portions.
With spatula, apply mayonnaise to each slice.
Dip in cheese and crumb mixture.
Place on slightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until tender.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, onion, green pepper, red pepper and celery seed. Boil vinegar, sugar and oil; let cool and pour over cabbage mixture. Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: churros
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over high heat.
Reduce heat to medium 5 minutes before adding the dough.
Roll dough into nickel size balls.
Drop into preheated oil. Fry until lightly browned. (Dough will expand as it is heated.) Remove from heat.
Drain. Coat with icing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone; cut in chunks.
Mix soups and broth well.
Combine chicken, rice and broth mixture.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange mallow ring
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ginger ale.
Chill until very thick.
Stir in marshmallows and orange sections.
Pour into a 1-quart ring mold or individual small molds.
Chill until firm. Makes 3 cups or 6 servings.

title: stage deli california chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, honey, sour cream and white pepper in a large bowl; mix well.
Add chicken, green onions, celery, raisins and almonds.
Toss gently to coat chicken well.
Chill well before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: tropical lemon cream pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; mix well.
Gradually add milk, stirring over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens; continue boiling gently one minute.
Remove from heat; slowly pour hot mixture into beaten eggs, stirring vigorously.
Return to low heat; cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon rind, lemon juice and butter.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.

title: blueberry cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Sift together cornmeal, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Add buttermilk.
Beat in egg and shortening.
Fold in
blueberries.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch skillet and bake 35 minutes.

title: chicken tostada
directions: Boil the chicken breast, shred with 2 forks.
Fry the tortillas in oil or use ready made shells.

title: broccoli bonanza
directions: Combine ingredients and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buffet meatballs
directions: Grate onion and mix with beef, egg, salt and pepper.
Form balls about 1-inch in diameter.
In a large saucepan, mix chili sauce, grape jelly and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil; drop meatballs and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: teahouse punch
directions: Combine hot water, nutmeg, allspice and cinnamon in saucepan. Bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add tea bags and steep 5 minutes.
Strain into pitcher. Add cold water, sugar, lemon juice and orange extract.
Mix well. Chill and serve over ice cubes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and savory meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg and garlic.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown meatballs in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, that have been mixed together, except rice. Cover; cook over low heat about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Serve over rice.

title: coconut bread
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients. Stir in coconut and orange or lemon peel.
Combine remaining ingredients (add to dry mixture all at once).
Stir until mixed well.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes in lightly greased loaf pan.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Cut zucchini in cubes.
Cut onion in pieces.
Saute in margarine until zucchini is tender.
Add sour cream, milk and salt. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of poppy seed and paprika.
Mix and serve.

title: strawberry sundae pie
directions: Stir 3/4 cup frosting and butter together until smooth; fold in cereal until well mixed.
Press on bottom and up sides of a greased 9-inch pie plate; freeze until firm.
Spread ice cream in crust; cover and freeze until firm.
Stir remaining frosting and milk together until smooth.
Just before serving, arrange fruit on pie.
Serve with sauce.

title: apricot bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, mix flour and baking powder.
Gradually add to butter mixture.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Press 2/3 of dough into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread on preserves.
Crumble remaining dough on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put half of crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth with electric mixer.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Beat at medium for 2 minutes.
Fold together the cream cheese and pudding mixture; pour on cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs on top.
Can be frozen or chilled.

title: barley pilaf
directions: Heat butter in large skillet.
Add onion.
Cook until soft and golden.
Add barley and stir over low heat until grains are coated with fat and lightly colored but not brown.
Transfer to large buttered casserole and add about 2/3 of the boiling chicken broth or enough to cover the barley generously.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover dish tightly and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir lightly with a fork and stir in the green onion, parsley and rest of broth.
Cook for about 15 minutes longer or until broth is absorbed and grains are puffy and tender.
Keep warm in low oven.
Toss in cashews just before serving.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well. Alternate dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1/4 cup dough onto lightly greased cookie sheet, spreading pumpkin shapes with spatula.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cookies should be firm and light brown.
Makes 32 cookies.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook together until thick, cool.
Pour over 1 quart strawberries, cleaned and cut up in a 9 inch pie crust.
Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/4 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler.
Heat over simmering water, stirring until melted.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Brown pork chops in oil until nice and brown.
Add can of soup and water.
Simmer about 30 minutes until chops are tender.
The soup makes very good gravy.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook cut ziti according to package directions; drain.
In a large bowl, combine cooked ziti, 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, parsley, egg, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
In a 3-quart casserole, pour 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce. Spread ziti mixture evenly over sauce. Top with remaining 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle on the Parmesan cheese. Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Makes about 8 servings.
(I use a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.)

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat egg and milk.
Sift in flour, salt, sugar and baking powder together.
To this, add egg and milk mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into hot grease (oil).

title: abbie's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and butter.
Add eggs and pecans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add the cheese spread and tomatoes, stirring until the cheese spread melts.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve hot with chips.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Combine vegetables.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly and leave in refrigerator overnight. Serves 12 to 16.
Great for cookout.

title: dinette cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Measure all ingredients into a large bowl.
Mix well and pour into pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.

title: crab spread
directions: Press crabmeat between paper towels to remove excess water out.
Combine crabmeat and green onions in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine cream cheese and next 6 ingredients.
Add to crabmeat and onion mixture, tossing to coat well.
Cover and chill 8 hours. Serve with assorted crackers.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: hog head cheese
directions: Boil skins and bones with chunks of onion, celery, spices, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Boil about 1 hour.
Add meat and pork tongue and heart, if desired.
Strain broth and set aside to cool.
Remove meat from bone; put through grinder on coarse.
Set aside.

title: blend of the bayou seafood casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter using double boiler.
Saute shrimp, onion, pepper and celery in 2 tbsp. butter.
Add to the first mixture.
Add soup mushroom, seasonings, crab meat, and rice.
Mix well, place in 2 qt. casserole, and top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350 about 20-30 minutes until bubbly.

title: simple pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating at high speed.
Turn mixer to low speed and gradually add flour.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box; cool.
Mix pudding as directed on box and cool.
Place half of cake on the bottom of a large bowl (glass punch bowl works best), then add 1/2 of pudding, 1/2 of cherry pie filling, 1/2 of blueberries, 1/2 of sliced bananas and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat with remaining ingredients and garnish.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine.
Simmer soup, cream cheese, pimentos, sour cream and shrimp.
Add sauteed vegetables.
Simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in greased tube pan. Cream butter and cheese. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and nuts. Stir until combined.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes before dumping.

title: skillet cobbler
directions: In a cast-iron skillet, empty can of fruit.
Pour cake mix on top of fruit.
Do not stir.
Slice stick of butter and place over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jello punch
directions: Cook sugar and water until just clear, 1 to 2 minutes.
Do not make syrup.
Add jello water, then pineapple juice, then lemon juice.
Put in coffee cans and freeze.
At serving time, defrost just long enough to make a slush-type drink.
Just before serving, add 1 quart of ginger ale.

title: tuna curry
directions: Heat tuna in prepared white sauce.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cut olives and remove pits; add to mixture.
Cube eggs; add to mixture. Blend in curry.
Serve hot over rice. Garnish with pimiento.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tortilla pinwheel appetizers
directions: Mix all.
Spread on soft tortillas; roll, cover and refrigerate a couple hours.
Cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices (electric knife works great).
Serve with salsa.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together except nuts.
Pour into a prepared pie crust. Place nuts in orderly fashion on top.
Bake at 350° from 45 to 60 minutes or until center is set.
Cool and serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: zucchini seafood impossible quiche
directions: Grease baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and spread in dish. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6. The Bisquick mix makes a crust on top.

title: parmesan sesame seed biscuits
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and cayenne.
Cut butter into flour mixture.
Add cheese and the buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly. Knead at least six times on pastry board.
Roll out to desired thickness or to about 1/2-inch thick.
Top with 1 tablespoon of toasted and cooled sesame seed.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the cheese.
Pour into a large casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with grated cheese and continue to bake until cheese begins to melt.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Used Italian dry bread crumbs too.
Great!

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Make okra as if making the salad mix.
Cook ground meat in skillet until brown and then add to the salad mix and add Worcestershire sauce, tarragon vinegar, lemon pepper, sweet basil, parsley and 1 clove garlic.

title: aunt helen's marinated carrots(copper pennies)
directions: Drain
cooked carrots and mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cool.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix together the coconut, Eagle Brand milk and confectioners sugar.
Chill for 1 hour. Roll into balls.
Keep balls chilled so they won't fall apart.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Mix soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, onion and green pepper until smooth.
Pour over carrots and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In 1 gallon water, cook beef until well done along with onion, pepper, cabbage and tomatoes.
Add mixed vegetables and potatoes and cook until done.
Then add remaining ingredients and cook until all flavors are blended.
Add more water.
This will make a large amount of soup, but it can be frozen for another time and will probably taste better then.
